title: mexican stack-up
directions: Place prepared ingredients on large platter in the following order:

bean dip, avocado (to keep avocado from browning, sprinkle lemon juice on top), taco seasoning and sour cream mixed together, chopped tomatoes, chopped green onions, black olives and grated cheese (on top).

title: holiday punch
directions: Pour in the cranberry juice and apple juice into the coffee urn.
Place cinnamon, cloves, and brown sugar into basket and let perk for 30 minutes.
Drink hot and enjoy.

title: princess loaf
directions: Wash and cook rice.
Beat eggs slightly.
Chop onion and braise in margarine.
Add herbs.
Combine all ingredients well and place in an oiled 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with brown gravy.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: dolly's shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook sausage, zucchini, green pepper, onion and garlic with oregano until done. Stir to separate meat. Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes or until done. Stir occasionally.
Makes 7 cups or 4 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine eggs and salt.
Place alternating layers of corn, mixture and crumbs in greased baking dish.
Dot each layer with butter.
Pour in milk.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon squares
directions: Toast bread slices.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread mixture on bread slices.
Toast in 450° oven for 10 minutes. These may also be frozen and toasted at a later time.

title: apple bread
directions: Beat the oil, apples, nuts, eggs and sugar by hand. Then add the flour, soda, salt and vanilla. Add raisins (optional). Bake at 350° in tube pan for 90 minutes or 2 loaf pans for 60 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Blend sugar, cocoa, flour and salt in saucepan.
Gradually add milk and beaten egg yolks.
Bring to a slow boil and cook until thick. Remove from heat, add butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Pour in cooled baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix eggs, flour, mustards, sugar and salt together.
Add milk and cook over a very low flame, stirring constantly.
When it starts to thicken, add vinegar and cook until it thickens.
Makes 1 quart.

title: kid's fun kaleidoscope
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler; add butter, egg and pecans.
When mixture is slightly cooled, add marshmallows.
Stir to coat.
Use wax paper 18-inches long and put down a heavy coat of coconut.
Pour mixture over coconut.
Roll into a log 1 1/2 to 2-inches.
Chill, slice and serve.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine 2 cups Flour, Yeast, Sugar, Cinnamon, Salt and Baking Soda.
Add Orange Juice, Water and Oil; beat on low speed until moistened.
Beat on high 3 minutes.
Stir in the Pecans, Apricots and remaining Flour to form a stiff batter.
Do not knead.
Grease two 8 x 4 x 2 inch loaf pans; sprinkle with cornmeal.
Spoon batter into pans; sprinkle with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350 for 35 - 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pans to cool on wire racks.
Slice and toast.
Yield 2 loaves.

title: hot dip
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Melt cheese in a double boiler and add other ingredients.
Serve in a fondue dish, keeping warm.
Use Doritos or crackers for dipping.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients; drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° to 350° until light brown.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, flour and powdered sugar.
Pack into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder and lemon juice.
Mix well and spread on crust. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Bring sauce to boil.
Put meat in and cook on medium heat for 15 minutes.
Remove and cool in refrigerator overnight.
Cut vegetables and place on skewer with meat.
Grill and baste with sauce.

title: jello rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and water and bring to a boil and boil 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add gradually 2 packages of red jello and boil 5 minutes more.
Pour into jars and seal. (Jello can be of choice.)

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cut up vegetables.
Mix all together.
Add salad dressing and Salad Supreme.
Mix together and refrigerate.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon juice; mix well. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set.
Top with sour cream.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Chill. Top with strawberries.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix ingredients and boil to soft ball stage or 234°.
Add butter and vanilla.
Let stand until cool.
Beat until creamy. Pour into buttered plate.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: crumb cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour into 11 x 16-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
While baking, mix sugar and margarine.
Add cinnamon and flour.
Mix into crumbs and cover top of cake.
Continue to bake crumbs and cake for 20 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: brown rice pizza
directions: Crust:
Beat egg. Add herb seasonings.
Add rice and mix thoroughly.
Oil pizza pan or pie plate.
Press mixture into pan thinly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes (can be stored in refrigerator/freezer at this stage).

title: zucchini pie
directions: Saute zucchini and onions in margarine; add spices.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add shredded cheese.
Add zucchini.
Press rolls into pie plate to form crust; add zucchini mixture.
Cover with sliced tomatoes and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes (cover edges with foil to prevent overbrowning).
Remove foil last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: shrimpies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with beater or blender.
Pour on English muffins.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serve whole or cut into wedges.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Pour into crust; chill at least 20 minutes.
Garnish with lemon slices or graham cracker crumbs.

title: split seconds
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Divide into 4 piles.
Shape each into a roll 13 inches long, 3/4 inch wide.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 4 inches apart.
Make a depression about 1/4 inch deep down the center of roll.
Fill with Jam.
Bake at 350 for 15-20 minutes, until light brown.
While still warm, cut diagonally.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together except whipping cream and confectioners sugar.
Put into baking dish and bake until toothpick comes out clean.	Cool completely.
Chop pudding into small pieces.
Whip 1/2 pint whipping cream and add small amount of confectioners sugar to taste.
Fold into pudding.
Top with a dollop of whipping cream when served.

title: eddie's peanut butter pie
directions: Combine oleo and crumbs and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese.
Add sugar, peanut butter, milk and whipped topping, beating well after each addition.
Spread onto crust.
Put in freezer.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together and put into mold or ice cube container and serve frozen.

title: chili corn bread casserole
directions: Combine ground beef and onions in a 10 x 10 x 2-inch dish. (Make certain to break up meat and spread over entire dish.)
Cook with microwave at High for 4 minutes.
Stir several times during cooking.
If using chuck, do not drain.
When using regular ground beef, you will want to remove excess grease.

title: black forest trifle
directions: Cut rolls lengthwise in half.
Arrange vertically around outside of 3-quart glass bowl (cut side out).
Chop coarsely more of rolls (enough for layer in bowl).
In large bowl, mix pudding as label directions state, using only 2 cups of milk.
Fold in Cool Whip except for 1/4 cup reserved for top.
Spoon half of pudding mixture into 3-quart bowl; top with chopped cake rolls, then half of cherry pie filling.
Top with remaining pudding mixture.
Make an indentation in center of pudding mixture; spoon in remaining cherry pie filling.
Cut some of reserved cake rolls crosswise in 1/2-inch slices.
Garnish with cake roll slices and reserved Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until cooled, at least 2 hours.

title: potato bake
directions: Grease 1-quart casserole.
Prepare the instant mashed potatoes, using package directions, except omit butter.
Fold in cream cheese. Stir in egg, onion and parsley. Blend well and transfer to well-greased 1-quart baking dish. Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchie cookies
directions: Cream fats and sugar together; add the other wet ingredients and mix with the other dry ingredients (quite a stiff mix).
Roll into small balls and space them out on a greased baking tray. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or on gas mark 4.

title: lemon roll
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, add yolks and vanilla, mix well. Add
sugar
and blend. Sift flour and baking powder and add
to egg
mixture.
Mix
well.
Pour
batter
into a large cookie sheet sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 to
25 minutes.
Invert
cake on cup towel and roll up.
Cool completely.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters and roll in cinnamon and sugar that has been mixed together.
Put in greased Bundt or angel food pan. Boil butter and brown sugar 1 minute and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir ice cream until soft; add coffee and almonds; mix well.
Put into pan over cookie crumbs.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, cut into squares and serve with chocolate sauce on top.

title: caramel icing
directions: Bring to a boil in a heavy, large pan 2 cups sugar and whipping cream.
In a small pan or skillet, caramelize 1/4 cup sugar.
Stir to keep from burning.
When caramelized, add to the cream and sugar mixture.
Cook until soft ball forms in cold water.
This only takes a few minutes.
Take off heat; add vanilla and margarine.
Beat with mixer until thick.
If too thick, add a little milk.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Beat egg yolks and milk. Stir egg and milk mixture into dry ingredients to form a smooth paste, then stir in remaining liquid.
Stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Continue stirring about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and butter.
Pour into a baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: sally's chop suey
directions: Saute pork in oil.
Add and simmer next 6 ingredients.
Stir in 1 can chop suey vegetables and 1 can bean sprouts.
Heat until warm.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: nancy duke's prize chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer until other ingredients are combined well.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.
This recipe doubles nicely for company.
Great served with salad and bread.

title: chicken with dumplings
directions: Prepare stewed chicken. When almost tender, sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Combine milk and oil. Add to dry ingredients. Stir just to moisten. Drop from tablespoon directly onto chicken in boiling broth. (Do not let batter drop into the liquid.) Cover tightly and return to boiling. Reduce heat (do not lift cover). Simmer 12 to 15 minutes until dumplings are done. Remove chicken and dumplings to hot platter. Keep hot while preparing gravy. Pour gravy over chicken and dumplings. Garnish with parsley. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix with buttermilk and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add liquid ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Do not knead. Refrigerate overnight.

title: graham cracker chews
directions: Line a greased 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet with crackers.
Bring to boil the brown sugar and margarine.
Pour over crackers. Sprinkle top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes only.
Cool in refrigerator.
Separate into bars.

title: tenderloin casserole
directions: Brown pork in oiled skillet. Spray 9 x 13 glass baking dish with Pam cooking spray. Place a layer of sliced potatoes into greased baking dish. Place diced onion on top of potatoes and then layer diced green peppers over onions. Transfer browned pork over into baking dish over green pepper layer. In separate bowl, mix soup and water and mix well. Pour soup mixture over meat to cover. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Mix marshmallows with pineapple and let stand awhile.
Make Jell-O according to directions.
When slightly jelled, whip it. Whip the whipping cream.
Break cake into small pieces.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese
directions: Cook broccoli (10 minutes) and rice according to directions. Mix soup and milk well.
Add broccoli and rice.
Add cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Thinly slice 1 stick margarine or butter and place pats on mixture, covering it.
Sprinkle on croutons.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine all except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place in a large rectangular dish.
Top with cheese, almonds and potato chips.

title: springtime spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve with assorted vegetables, celery, carrots or other dippers.

title: mama ellen's chow chow
directions: Cut up all vegetables in small cubes.
Mix in 1/4 cup salt. Let this mixture set overnight in refrigerator.

title: cozze alla marinara
directions: After cleaning mussels (shells) place in deep pot with approximately 1/2-inch of water.
Place over medium heat with pan covered.
When water boils enough for the mussels to begin to open, add garlic, pepper, parsley, salt and tomatoes.
Mix and continue heating over medium heat for approximately 5 minutes. Serve with garlic bread.

title: chow chow
directions: Pour boiling water over vegetables; let stand for 10 minutes, then drain.
Add seasonings.
Boil for 15 to 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Cook until thick, about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Great over hot biscuits.

title: cheez whiz spuds
directions: Pimentos can be added whenever you think of them.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: The potatoes may be peeled or just scrubbed well.
Slice them in 1/2-inch thick rounds.
Place in a crock-pot.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Sprinkle with Tex-Joy.
Put a stick of margarine on top and plug in the pot.
Place setting on high for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: hawaiian kabobs
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Place pineapple chunks and vegetables in a large bowl; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine reserved pineapple juice with soy sauce, olive oil, brown sugar and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Pour over vegetable mixture; cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove pineapple and vegetables from marinade and reserve marinade. Alternate pineapple, green peppers, onion, mushrooms and tomatoes on skewers.
Grill kabobs for 20 minutes or until soft, turning and basting with marinade frequently.
Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oyster and sausage patties
directions: Mix all as meat loaf.
Shape into patties and fry.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add soups and cheese.
Mix well. Add chopped broccoli and rice.
Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, soup, mustard, pepper, Worcestershire and salt; boil until thick, about 5 minutes.
Add onion and green pepper.
Arrange carrots in layers with onions and peppers, pour boiling marinade over carrots.
Place in fridge at least 24 hours. Serve hot or cold.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Mix all together; add small amount of apples while using mixer and then add the rest of apples and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
In mixer, beat eggs, sugar and flour.
While beating, melt margarine.
Add hot water.
Add powdered milk to sugar/flour mixture.
Pour butter on flour mixture.
Add baking powder and lemon (or orange or vanilla extract).
Put in pan immediately.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Heat all ingredients until boiling.
Pour over shredded leaf lettuce and mix well.

title: simmered chicken
directions: Place all
ingredients
in large pot.
Heat to boiling. Cover and reduce
heat.
Simmer
2 1/2 hours, then discard bay leaves, celery tops and onions.

title: chicken lo mein
directions: In skillet, heat oil.
Brown meat in same pan.
Bring broth, water, ginger, pepper, teriyaki sauce and garlic to boil.
Add vermicelli.
Simmer, covered, 8 minutes, stirring often.
Add vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 4 minutes. Stir in onions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and butter.
Add sugar, flavorings and baking powder.
Mix well. Add eggs, beating after each.
Add milk and flour alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Place in a cold oven and set the temperature to 350°.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Break up half of the cookies and line bottom of cake pan (13 x 9-inches).
Pour melted butter over cookies.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar until spreadable.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cookies.
Mix pudding per package directions and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Crumble remaining cookies on top of cake.
Chill.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls in jelly roll pan, forming a crust. Bake at 350° until light brown, about 10 minutes; cool.

title: easy "sticky buns"
directions: Cut 1 loaf into 16 pieces and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch bread pan.

title: fried squash balls
directions: Mix together and chill for 1 hour.
Form into balls and fry in grease.

title: quick soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Simmer until hot.
Ready to serve.

title: cherry coconut bar cookies
directions: In bowl, stir rest of these ingredients into eggs.
Dump onto baked pastry (above).
No need to cool pastry first.
Bake another 20 to 25 minutes until edges are brown and top toasty in 350° oven in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Serves 9 to 12 pieces.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugars, cornstarch and milk until ball is formed in water.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring quickly.
Spread in buttered pan; refrigerate.

title: oriental spaghetti quickie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
While spaghetti is cooking, stir-fry vegetables with sauce.
Drain spaghetti and toss with vegetables.

title: hot spice cider
directions: Heat apple cider.
Add cloves, stick cinnamon and allspice. Continue to heat about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Serve piping hot.
Great for a crowd of 25 to 30 .
Easy to scale down for a smaller group.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix well sugar and cracker crumbs.
Melt in double boiler, peanut butter and butter.
In separate bowl, melt chocolate chips. Press graham cracker crust into 11 x 14-inch pan.
Blend well. Pour chocolate over mixture in pan.
Let set 15 to 20 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: jeane's bread machine bread
directions: Add Quaker oats with white flour, salt, milk, sugar and yeast into bread machine.
Follow instructions of your machine manufacturer.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers or eat as a salad.

title: gruzzlenuckles
directions: Mix all together.
Press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: easy apple butter
directions: Mix together.
Put in a large cake pan.
Bake 3 hours at 350°. Bake, covered.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Fry onion in margarine until margarine is melted. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix all ingredients and pour into pan. Top with crushed corn flakes or potato chips. Bake 1 1/2 hours, uncovered, at 400°.

title: corn bake
directions: Combine in large bowl creamed corn, whole kernel corn, oleo, sour cream, eggs, sugar and muffin mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and white sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time and beat thoroughly after each one. Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in a tube pan, greased and floured.

title: ham and potatoes au gratin
directions: Layer the ham and potatoes in a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Melt 3 tablespoons margarine in a saucepan; add the onion and cook until golden.
Blend in flour.
Add milk gradually and cook, stirring, until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper. Pour over the ham mixture and sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Dot with remaining margarine.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Add all ingredients. Beat and pour into tube pan.
Do not grease.
Bake 1 hour.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Bring oleo, buttermilk and cocoa to a boil.
Pour over sugar. Add vanilla.
Beat until icing is spreading consistency.
Frost cake still in pan (Chocolate Sheath Cake).

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Pour this over the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
It will rise and then fall in the center.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in large pot and stir flour smoothly into it. Stir chicken broth into flour mixture.
Add cream.
Cook this mixture over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add wine, salt, pepper, spaghetti, mushrooms, green peppers and cooked chicken.
You may either turn this mixture into a baking dish and sprinkle the cheese on top or layer this mixture and the Cheddar cheese until all of
it is in the dish.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: party ham
directions: You will also need a Reynolds baking bag.
Place flour in bag and shake.
Remove skin and fat from ham.
Lightly score the ham. Rub honey all over ham.
Stud the ham with whole cloves.
Place ham in bag and tie bag.
Make 6 small slits in top of bag.
Place a meat thermometer into the thickest part of ham.
Do not touch the bone.
Bake until thermometer reads 140° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: chicken in the oven
directions: Place chicken between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap and flatten to 1/2-inch thickness, using a meat mallet. Top each chicken breast with 1 green chili and 1 slice of the cheese. Roll up, securing with a toothpick. Whisk together egg and 2 tablespoons water in a shallow bowl. Dip chicken rolls in egg mixture dredged in crushed chips. Place rolls in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing. Serve with salsa and garnish.

title: split pea soup
directions: Combine water, split peas, ham, onion and seasonings in 5-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave at High 40 minutes, stirring several times during cooking.

title: no knead bread rolls
directions: Dissolve 1 package yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Scald and cool 1/2 cup milk.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add to yeast.
Then add 2 cups flour and beat well.
Add 1 egg, 3 tablespoons melted butter and 1 cup flour.
Let rise until double.
Make into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: night before mashed potatoes
directions: Boil and drain potatoes. Whip potatoes, adding cream cheese and sour cream. Continue beating until fluffy and smooth. Add salt and pepper. Place in a buttered 9x13 baking dish. Dot generously with butter and sprinkle with seasoned salt. Cover with foil and refrigerate. Potatoes can be frozen at this stage and thawed before baking. Bake, covered with foil, for 15 minutes at 325 degrees. Continue baking, uncovered, 20
minutes. Serves 8-10.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery, grapes and walnuts.
Turn fruit mixture into a romaine lined salad bowl.
Chill. Combine salad dressing, sugar and lemon juice.
Whip cream until soft peaks form.
Fold into salad dressing.
Spoon mixture over chilled apple mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
To serve fold dressing into fruit mixture.

title: roast venison
directions: Arrange bacon on top of backstrap or steaks. Place on rack in shallow roasting pan. Broil 10-15 minutes with small amount of water in pan. Remove fat drippings from pan. Place meat and bacon back in pan. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over roast. Cover with foil. Bake 2 1/2-3 hours, turning after 1 hour. You can double all ingredients except meat and add potatoes and carrots, or you can make gravy from the drippings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, flour and nutmeg in a large saucepan. Let sit 20 minutes until syrup forms.
Bring peach mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Blend in almond extract and butter.
Roll out half the pastry to fit an 8 x 12 x 2-inch dish.
Spoon half of peach mixture into buttered dish.
Top with cut pastry.
Bake at 475° for 12 minutes.
Spoon remaining peaches over baked pastry.
Roll out remaining pastry and cut into 1/2-inch strips.
Arrange over peaches in lattice design. Bake at 475° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: carolyn's chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each piece of chicken between two sheets of plastic wrap. Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Sprinkle with pepper.
Top each with a piece of ham and 3 tablespoons of Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up in a jelly roll fashion. Tuck in sides.
Secure each roll with a wooden toothpick.
Combine cereal, paprika and garlic powder in a shallow dish.
Dip each roll in milk.
Dredge in cereal mixture.
Place in baking dish coated in vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: black walnut jiffy cake
directions: Drop ingredients into large bowl of electric mixer in order given. Beat at high speed 5 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool upright before removing from pan.

title: tomato broccoli toss
directions: Cover bottom of skillet with generous amount of oil.
Add broccoli, onion and tomatoes.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Broccoli should be tender, not mushy.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and quickly cover.
Allow to stand for 3 minutes.
Stir together and serve.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate the potatoes.
Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add well beaten eggs and blend well.
Add grated potatoes, spices and milk.
Beat well together.
Add the grated lemon and orange skins. Pour mixture in a well-buttered pan and bake slowly about an hour. It may be served hot or cold, cut in slices.
It is delicious when served at luncheon with a glass of fresh cold milk.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add water and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O powder.
Let cool.
Arrange strawberries in pie shell and pour strawberry-sugar mixture over strawberries.
Cool in refrigerator.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: geri's cheese cake
directions: Blend first 2 ingredients and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press firmly against bottom and 2 1/2 inches up side of spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add remaining sugar and vanilla extract.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Blend in sour cream. Spread in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until firm.
Turn oven off.
Leave oven door ajar and allow cheese cake to stay in oven for 1 hour.
Chill overnight.
Top with canned cherries before serving.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Heat shortening, molasses and brown sugar just to melt.
Cool and add eggs.
Sift flour.
Add remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Chill overnight and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter and lightly fry strips of chicken breast.
In baking pan, melt remaining butter and place thawed broccoli on top.
Sprinkle cheese (3/4 of it).
Arrange chicken strips on cheese.
Mix undiluted soup with wine.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: easy do fudge
directions: Combine butter or margarine, sugar and milk in saucepan over low heat. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add Marshmallow Creme, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts. Stir until marshmallow and chocolate are dissolved. Pour into buttered dish or pan.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, vinegar, cooking oil, salt and celery seed; keep warm.
Grate cabbage and have a 1/2 cup of sugar ready. Put a layer of slaw in bowl and add a few slices of onion. Sprinkle with some sugar.
Continue layers until sugar is used up. Pour hot mixture over this and do not stir.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Stir just before serving.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into 9 x 13 pan.
Tilt until bottom is covered with oil.
Put remaining ingredients into pan. Stir with a fork or spoon until blended (about 2 minutes).
Scrape sides and spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cooled cake may be sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in corn flakes and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet lined with foil.
Put in oven and turn oven off.
Leave until cool.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour; add milk, form ball of dough and fold in drained sausage.
Roll dough on floured pastry sheet and cut into small biscuits.
Place on baking pan and bake at 450°.

title: pickled beets and eggs
directions: Drain beets; reserve 1 cup juice.
In saucepan combine vinegar, sugar, salt, cloves, onion and beet juice.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Add beets and simmer covered 10 minutes.
Shell eggs and place in a gallon jar.
Pour in beets and juice; stir gently.
Cool and refrigerate covered at least 24 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix by hand and form into balls (walnut sized).
Place on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: pineapple sour cream pound cake
directions: Drain 1 cup syrup from pineapple.
Discard syrup.
Set pineapple aside.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, and baking soda; stir to blend.
Make a well into the center of the dry ingredients.
In a separate bowl, combine eggs, sour cream, pineapple, oil, vanilla and lemon peel; blend well.
All at once, add egg mixture to well in dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool in pan 20 minutes; gently turn out of pan onto wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: impossible cookies
directions: Beat egg; add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Form 1-inch balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Let cookies harden on cookie sheet a few minutes.
Makes 30 to 40 cookies.
(This does not have any flour.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash.
Saute onions, salt and pepper in oleo.
Mix with cooked, drained squash.
Beat egg; mix with cream-style corn.
Add to other ingredients.

title: spicy chicken with broccoli
directions: Cut chicken into 2 1/2-inch pieces.
Toss with cornstarch, salt and pepper in medium bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 20 minutes. Boil broccoli 1 minute.
Drain and rinse in cold water immediately.
Cut onions diagonally into 1-inch pieces.
Heat wok or skillet until very hot.
Add oil and spread around.
Add red pepper, garlic, sugar and ginger; stir-fry 10 seconds.
Add chicken and stir-fry until white.
Add broccoli and onion; stir-fry until broccoli is hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Place in baking dish. Cover with bacon slices.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in jello mold and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix all ingredients and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except sour cream together.
Pour half into 9 x 13-inch pan; put in freezer for 15 minutes.
Spread sour cream over set mixture and pour rest of mixture over.
Refrigerate until set.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Chill dough for at least 3 hours.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Space two inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for exactly 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and allow to cool for 8 minutes.
(Cookies will not appear to be done when you remove them from oven; they will solidify.
This will make them chewy.)

title: pull taffy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and vinegar, without stirring, until 252°. Add butter and soda; remove from fire.
Pour into buttered tin and when sufficiently cool, grease hands with butter and pull.
Cut into pieces and wrap in wax paper.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and separate into bite-sized pieces.
Simmer onion and celery until tender.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Bake in well-greased pan, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat and saute onion in pot.
Remove excess fat and season to taste.
Add 2 cans V-8 juice and saute a few minutes. Add 1 1/2 cups water.
Add raw rice and stir in well.
Start putting in shredded cabbage, a little at a time, until all is wilted.

title: coconut refrigerator cake
directions: Mix eggs, water, oil, cake mix and vanilla instant pudding. Bake cake in greased and floured cake pan for 25 minutes at 350°. After cooling, split to make 4 layers.
Stack with filling made of frozen coconut, 1 1/2 c. sugar and sour cream.
Store in refrigerator in air tight container for 3 to 5 days.
When ready to serve, mix softened cream cheese, 1/2 c. sugar, 1/2 c. confectioners' sugar and vanilla.
Fold in cool whip and frost top and sides of cake and add coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: texas cantaloupe chiffon cake
directions: Peel and seed cantaloupes.
Puree enough cantaloupe in a blender to make 2 cups.

With a mixer, beat 1 1/2 cups of the cantaloupe puree, 1/4 cup water and cake mix until well blended. Bake in an ungreased angel food cake pan at 350° for 40 minutes. Refer to package for cooling directions.
With a melon baller, make as many melon balls as possible with the remaining cantaloupe.

title: bavarian delight
directions: Line a long dish with slices of angel food cake.
Pour over the cake a mixture of the jello that has been dissolved in 1 cup hot water and mixed with the frozen strawberries.
When the jello has congealed, cover with a layer of the pudding that has been mixed with the milk.
Optional topping could be coconut or whipped cream.

title: cheesy fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, over medium heat, melt margarine and cream cheese, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Sift together the powdered sugar and cocoa and add to the cheese and margarine; mix.
Add other ingredients (vanilla and nuts); stir. Place fudge in thickness desired in a buttered dish and place in the refrigerator.

title: quick and easy no fail fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in pan except vanilla; stir until chips are melted.
Add vanilla and pour into pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: apple crisp
directions: Add oil and egg (beaten) to the topping mixture. Put apples in dish. Cover with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Pour on topping. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in 2-quart glass bowl. Microwave on High until candy mixture boils.
Stir.
Clip on microwave-safe candy thermometer.
Microwave on High until mixture reaches 236°.
Stir in chips until smooth.
Blend in marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased (Pam) 12 x 8-inch pan; cool.
Fudge will be firm, but soft.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter.
Let stand about 15 minutes.
Pour into pastry lined 9-inch pie pan.
Dot with butter. Add top crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Cut and open slits in top crust.
Bake at 425° until syrup boils with heavy bubbles that do not burst, 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: custard pie filling
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and nutmeg last.
Add strained, scalded milk.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: allison house inn granola
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine oats and almonds in bowl.
Mix in apple juice concentrate.
Add sugar and cinnamon and toss. Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in coconut and bake until golden, about 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool.
Add cranberries to granola.
Store in airtight container at room temperature.
Makes 5 cups.
Cranberries and almonds can be chopped coarsely if you prefer.

title: peggy's shortbread
directions: Sieve the flour and add the sugar.
Rub in the butter and then work the mixture into a ball with a knife.
Butter a baking tray and spread in the mixture.
Bake in a preheated oven at 190°C (375°F) for 25 minutes or until browned.
Remove from oven and cut into squares.
Sprinkle with caster sugar.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onion until loses red color.
Add tomatoes and simmer all in a saucepan at least a half hour.

title: spicy apple cheese squares
directions: In medium bowl, cream margarine and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and nuts and mix until well combined. Reserve one cup of mixture and set aside.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool slightly.
Spread half of the apple butter over baked crust.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix until smooth.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower to 350° and bake for 35 minutes, until firm.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo and mix with 2 cups cracker crumbs.
Mix sugar and cream cheese with Cool Whip.
Make first layer of cracker crumbs.
Add 2 cans of pie filling for second layer.
For third layer, spread cream cheese mixture.
For the fourth layer, put on top 1 cup graham cracker crumbs with 1/2 stick melted oleo. Refrigerate overnight, if possible, before serving.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients in large saucepan.
Stir and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and cereal; shape into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar or coconut.
Store in airtight container.

title: pea salad 1
directions: Place lettuce in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Pour peas over lettuce.
Add onions.
Mix margarine with sour cream and pour over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: cucumber-onion-pepper salad
directions: Cut or slice cucumber, onion and pepper into bite-size pieces. Add olive oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Mix well. Place bowl covered with Saran Wrap, together with salad plates and forks, in freezer for 10 to 15 minutes before serving. Serve immediately.

title: miracle cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make small cookies.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven and add enough water to cover well.
Add onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Stir and add all other ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and gradually add flour.
Stir constantly.
Add asparagus juice, making paste.
Add milk and stir until thick.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add cheese and mushrooms.
Put peas, then asparagus in bottom of baking dish. Pour sauce over.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot throughout.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: natalie haughton's chocolate walnut crunch cookies(from "365 great chocolate desserts")
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium size bowl, using an electric mixer set at medium speed, beat together the butter, sugar, Espresso powder, vanilla extract and salt until the mixture is fluffy, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Beat in the cocoa and flour until well blended.
Stir in the chocolate chips.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, cheese and butter well.
Add hash browns to the mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and sprinkle with bacon pieces and bake to 20 minutes.

title: cashew topped broccoli
directions: Place large size (14 x 20-inch) oven cooking bag in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange broccoli spears in bag, placing stems to outside of baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over broccoli spears.
Close bag with nylon tie, rubber bands, string or 1/2-inch strip cut from open end of bag.
Make 6 half inch slits in top.
Microcook on 100% power for 5 to 6 minutes or until broccoli is tender, turning dish once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake 2 cake layers according to directions on box.
Let cool. Mix
instant
vanilla
pudding
with
milk.
Set aside. Crumble 1 cake
layer
in
a	large
serving	bowl.
Pour 1/2 vanilla pudding
mix
over	this.
Next
pour 1/2 pie filling. Spread 1/2 of pineapple over this.
Then add 1/2 Cool Whip and sprinkle package of coconut on top.	Repeat.
May garnish with pecans if you like.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits according to package directions and cool 15 minutes. Melt oleo and cheese roll and add to grits.
Beat eggs with milk and stir in grits.
Pour into greased dish and top with cornflakes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (double for 10 people).

title: corn pudding
directions: Add corn to beaten eggs, then add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add buttermilk, egg and cranberry sauce.
Stir well; do not beat.
Stir in nuts. Spoon batter into a well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 5/8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: polly's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together first six ingredients until well blended.
Then add remaining ingredients, mix until smooth.
Grease and flour 3 one pound coffee cans or 2 loaf pans.
Divide batter evenly into pans and Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: marinated grouper
directions: Combine oils, mustard, lemon juice, rosemary, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Marinate fish in mixture 2 hours or longer. Drain marinade and reserve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Coat biscuits with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Grease Bundt pan.
Alternate sugared quarters with nuts in pan.
Bring to a boil 1 cup sugar, 1 stick oleo and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Stir in cold water.
Cool in refrigerator but do not jell.
Blend pretzels, sugar and butter. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool. Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread mixture over cooked pretzels.
Add fresh fruit to Jell-O (optional) and pour mixture over cream cheese.
Chill.

title: b~b~q sandwich meat
directions: Cook pork meat until tender.
Let cool.
Pull meat from bones.
Mash meat.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Place in baking pan. Pour ketchup or barbecue sauce over top.
Place in 300° oven and bake for 30 minutes.

title: black bean and rice salad
directions: Combine rice, beans, tomato, cheese and parsley in a large bowl.
Pour dressing and lime juice over rice mixture.
Toss lightly.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: delicious cherry plytsok(bars)
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, except for pie filling. Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour batter into pan and even out with spatula.
Spread cherry filling on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can take part of dough to make crisscross strips on top of pie filling.

title: custard pudding
directions: Mix well.
Cook until it thickens.
This makes 1 pie or double for dish of pudding.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems and cook with onions in 1 tablespoon butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in ham and cheese.
Set aside.

title: mirjham's german turtle cake
directions: Unwrap caramels first.
Make cake mix according to directions. Pour 1/2 the batter into 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into hollowed round of sourdough bread.
Use bread pieces as scoopers.

title: cheesy hash brown casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix ingredients and press in pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: overnight roast
directions: Nine
p.m.:
Braise
roast
on both sides (stove top or grill).
Place roast in baking dish.
Sprinkle with all of the onion soup mix.
Add water, enough to come halfway up sides of roast.
Cover
top completely with heavy-duty foil or 2 sheets regular foil.
This should make container steamproof.
Cook in 225°
oven
about
hours.
Go
to bed.
Roast will be ready tomorrow a.m.

title: kahlua
directions: Use a 1/2-gallon dark bottle.
In a 4-quart saucepan, mix coffee, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Take pan off burner and let stand 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vodka slowly.
Score vanilla bean in several places and put in bottle.
Add liquid and put in a dark place.
Shake at least once a week for six weeks.
The longer it sets, the better.

title: easy cheesecake supreme
directions: To prepare crust:
Combine the 3/4 cup flour, the 3 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of the lemon peel.
Cut in butter or margarine until crumbly.
Stir in 1 slightly beaten egg yolk and 1/4 teaspoon of vanilla.
Pat 1/3 of the dough onto the bottom of an 8-inch or 9-inch spring-form pan (with sides removed).
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes or until golden; cool.
Butter sides of pan; attach to bottom.
Pat remaining dough onto sides of the pan, about 1 3/4 inches high.
Beat softened cream cheese, remaining lemon peel and remaining vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in 1 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and salt; stir into cream cheese mixture.
Add 2 eggs and 1 egg yolk; beat until blended.
Add milk.
Turn into crust lined pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 300°; bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Loosen sides of cheesecake from pan with a spatula.
Cool 30 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool 2 hours longer.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring to a boil the oil, salt, water, pepper, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over vegetables while still hot.
Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep
for a long time.

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: In a bowl, combine the cucumbers and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate with water in microwave-safe bowl on Medium for 3 minutes.
Remove and stir to melt completely.
Add sugar. Microwave on Medium power for approximately 4 more minutes.
Add liqueur and butter; mix well.
Store in fridge.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Stir together pudding mix and pineapple until pudding is dissolved.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir and chill.

title: roasted red pepper dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a food processor or blender; mix on high until smooth. Chill, then serve.

title: mediterranean  christmas bread
directions: Dissolve yeast, 1/3 of sugar, in small bowl with warm water. In a large bowl, mix rest of sugar with cardamom, salt, egg whites, milk, and oil. Add yeast and rest of ingredients. Mix well to blend. Knead on floured board 5 minutes until smooth, elastic. Shape into ball, place in sprayed 8 inch round cake pan. Cover with damp cloth, let dough rise to double. Bake 350° 35-40 minutes until golden brown.

title: sandy's 1-2-3-4 muffins
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 30 muffins.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer each ingredient in large bowl.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: meltaways
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add vanilla, flour and nuts. Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° (will be light in color).
Roll in 10x sugar while warm.

title: orange tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags; brew for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add marmalade, sugar and lemon juice.
Heat until marmalade has dissolved, then serve hot.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together butter, nuts and flour.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and 6 ounces Cool Whip.
Spread on top of crust. Mix pudding with milk (chocolate, vanilla or your choice of pudding).
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Spread 6 ounces Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: mother's day fruit salad
directions: Into a large bowl, peel and cut orange into pieces.
Peel and slice banana.
Peel and cut an apple into pieces.
Peel and cut pear into pieces.
Add yogurt, spoon of honey and walnuts (if you would like).
Mix them together and serve!

title: deep dark chocolate cake(mixes in five minutes)
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients except for boiling water.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer, stir in boiling water (batter will be thin). Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans or three 8-inch pans, or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers, 35 to 40 minutes for oblong pan, or until tester inserted in middle comes out clean. Remove from pans. Cool completely. Top with favorite frosting.

title: basic crepe batter
directions: Sift flour and salt. Beat eggs and add milk and melted butter after it's cooled.
Add to flour and mix well.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Melt a little butter in a frying pan; don't let it brown.

When hot, add about 2 tablespoons of batter to pan and quickly swirl the pan so it covers bottom. Experiment until you find the right amount of batter and right heat. Turn crepe. Because they are so thin, they are wonderful for stuffing anything.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Cook
chicken,	remove bones and skin. Cut up and place in baking
dish.
Mix	chicken
broth	and
soup, beating and stirring until smooth. Pour over chicken.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of chicken soup

title: peachy punch
directions: Thaw 1 package frozen peaches.
Mix thawed peaches, wine, lemon juice and fruit punch; pour on frozen peaches in chilled punch bowl.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale; garnish with mint sprigs.
(To keep punch cold, another package of peaches can be added.)
Makes 24 servings.

title: vegetable chili
directions: In olive oil, saute green pepper and onion.
Add tomatoes (chopped or blended).
Add picante sauce, cumin and chili powder. Add corn, zucchini and kidney beans.
Cook over low heat 30 minutes.
Serve as is or with rice.

title: bill lundy's peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk, water and sugar.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Add vanilla, nuts and peanut butter.
Beat well (not too long as it will harden).
Put into a greased dish.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk, beat until thick, pour into crust. Put bananas over pudding.
Squeeze pineapple to remove juice, sprinkle pineapple on top, cover with cool whip, sprinkle pecans on top.
Chill well.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter or margarine and sugars. Add pudding mix, eggs and vanilla.
Combine the flour and baking soda; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: dump cake
directions: Put cherry pie filling in the bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 in. cake pan.
Put pineapple over cherries.
Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple layer.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle nut over
batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: apple stuffing
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Cool.
Add bread, egg, seasoning and apples and mix thoroughly, moistening with the stock until wet but not soupy.
Place in heavily buttered small baking dish and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: everlasting slaw
directions: Combine all vegetables.
In saucepan, mix the vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Bring to a boil; stir until sugar is melted.
Pour over vegetables.
Store in glass container.
Do not use plastic.
The slaw will keep until you use it.

title: garlic loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 8 ingredients and mix well. Heat milk, water and margarine together until mixture is 120° to 130°.
Blend two mixtures together with eggs and beat with a wooden spoon about 3 to 5 minutes to make a stiff batter.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to box directions. Drain and rinse in cold water.

title: vegetable snack mix
directions: Open crescent rolls and place on cookie sheet to make crust. Bake.
Let cool.
Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese and buttermilk salad dressing (enough to flavor).
Spread on crust.
Sprinkle finely cut vegetables over cream cheese mix.
Cover with waxed paper and press down.
Refrigerate 4 or 5 hours.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: peoples puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter together in microwave or in saucepan over low heat.
Pour cereal in large bowl and pour chocolate mixture.
Stir gently until well coated.
Put powdered sugar in large paper bag.
Add cereal and shake gently until pieces are coated. Pour out on two cookie sheets. Spread in a single layer and let dry until firm, about 1 hour.

title: stuffed round steak
directions: Beat and tenderize meat.
Mix seasonings from cooking bag with other ingredients to form paste.
Then spread onto the meat.
Roll up in jelly roll fashion and secure with string.
Place in cooking bag.
Cook at 300° for two hours or until desired doneness. Remove from bag.
Thicken gravy left in bag with cornstarch and pour over cooked meat.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Combine well drained cherries, pineapple bits and orange sections.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Combine sugar, 1/4 cup cream and lemon juice with eggs and cook in double boiler until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Whip remaining cream and fold into egg mixture.
Pour sauce over fruit mixture and mix lightly.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Serve on lettuce leaf and garnish with whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: beets in citrus sauce
directions: Cook beets whole until tender.
Drain, reserving liquid, peel and slice thin.
Pour liquid into pot.
Add grated peel, juice of 1 lemon, sugar, salt, cloves and orange juice concentrate. Dissolve cornstarch in just enough water to make smooth paste and add to mixture.
Beat mixture with whisk and cook until it becomes clear.
Add sliced beets and butter; heat.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican rice salad
directions: Combine eggs, rice, onions, celery, chiles and cheese in large mixing bowl.
Blend sour cream, lemon juice, picante sauce and seasonings.
Pour over egg mixture; mix well.
Chill.
Serve on salad greens and top with tomato.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken
directions: Grease baking dish with oleo.
Shred or chop beef and make layer in bottom of dish.
Wrap bacon around chicken and lay on top of beef.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over all.
Bake uncovered at 275° for 3 hours.

title: pot of pasta
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain.
Mix in sour cream while macaroni is warm.
While macaroni is cooking, brown the hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, Ragu and tomato sauce.
In one large casserole (or 2 medium), layer macaroni and sour cream, meat and sauce and Mozzarella cheese alternately until gone.
(I usually do it twice in 2 medium casseroles or 3 times in a large bowl.)
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes (covered, except last 10 minutes).

title: malted milk ball pie
directions: In a bowl, blend softened ice cream with crumbled milk balls and milk.
Spread onto pie crust; freeze until firm.
In another bowl, blend cocoa and Cool Whip together.
Spread over frozen ice cream.
Freeze for 1/2 hour.

title: powder sugar pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter
and
eggs one at a time.
Mix well in, add flour and
milk,
a
little
at a time, mix well.
Put pudding mix in
last.
Beat
egg
whites
stiff, fold in last. Bake in 9-inch tube
cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 250° or 255°according
to
your
stove
heat.
Cool for 15 minutes before turning pan up to come out.

title: coconut cake
directions: This cake is made in stages and needs to be made two days ahead of time.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and corn syrup.
Place on heat; bring to a boil and cook until mixture is thick and clear. Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
Pour part of cooled glaze in prepared pastry shell.
Arrange strawberries and cover with remaining glaze.
Top with whipped topping to serve.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain juice off 1 can of beets.
Add remaining ingredients together (except cloves) and boil until thick.
Pour over beets and cloves.
Put in refrigerator until cold.

title: chocolate graham cracker delight
directions: Finely chop 1/2 package chocolate.
Heat remaining chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk in saucepan over low heat.
Stir until melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese.
Add remaining milk and chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in chopped chocolate. Spoon into pie crust.
Freeze at least 4 hours.
Let stand 1 hour before serving.
Keep stored in freezer.

title: cherry divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add gelatin and beat until gelatin is dissolved.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and water and bring to boiling point, stirring until sugar is thoroughly dissolved.
Continue boiling to the firm ball stage (250° to 252°).
Slowly pour syrup into egg.

title: holly wreaths
directions: Cream together butter and cheese.
Add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly.
Beat in vanilla.
Fill cookie press with dough. Press dough through star plate in circular motion on ungreased cookie sheet to form wreaths.
Gently push ends together.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet at once to cooling racks. Yield: 2 dozen.

title: peach sauce
directions: In saucepan, mix peaches, sugar and orange juice.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer about 15 minutes or until thick (don't cover).
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice, vanilla and almond extract.
Excellent on pound cake.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple in greased 8 X 8 glass baking dish. Mix sugar & flour together. Sprinkle sugar/flour mixture over pineapple. Layer cheese on top of flour mixture. Sprinkle crackers over cheese. Pour melted butter over top. Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 30 minutes. Serve hot. Great with pork or poultry!

title: strawberry delight
directions: Slice pound cake and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place strawberries all over cake.
Beat condensed milk and cream cheese and pour over cake.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread in food processor.
Chill. Scoop centers from bread you prefer.
Fill bread cavities with dip mixture.
Cut bread centers into cubes.
(May be toasted and used to dip with or used plain.)

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in unbaked crust at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: double chocolate banana loaf
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, cocoa, sugars, baking powder, soda and salt.
Puree bananas in blender to measure 1 1/2 cups. Stir banana puree, margarine, eggs and vanilla into dry mixture. Mix until blended.
Stir in chocolate and almonds.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven 60 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pan to rack.
Cool before slicing.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread layer of pineapple, cherries and cake mix.
Place thinly sliced oleo over the first 3 layers. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Do not stir; leave in layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Make cake according to package directions.
Slice strawberries. Mix glaze and sliced strawberries in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix together Cool Whip, sour cream and 10X powered sugar to taste. Cut cake into chunks.
In trifle bowl layer cake, strawberries and Cool Whip.
Repeat layers until bowl is full. Refrigerate and serve.

title: speedy quiche
directions: Saute Spam and onions in oil until very tender.
Spoon into lightly greased 10-inch deep pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese. Mix remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour evenly into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: chicken divan
directions: Brown chicken in oil, stirring occasionally.
Add water, broccoli and soup.
Bring to a boil; stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Arrange chicken, broccoli and rice mixture on serving platter.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4. Less than 350 calories per serving.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add Worcestershire sauce, ketchup and garlic salt.
Fold in shredded crabmeat.
Serve cold with chips or crackers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, then chips and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together; layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Crush wafers; place 1/2 in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs one at
time; beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into pan.
Drain pineapple; add to whipped cream. Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix crumbs with 1/2 of the melted butter and press over bottom and sides of 10-inch pie pan.
Melt rest of butter in skillet and add onions.
Saute until soft but not brown.
Spread over cracker crumbs.
Beat eggs lightly and add salt, pepper and milk.
Blend with whisk.
Pour over onions.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Preheat oven.
Serves 4.

title: the best play dough
directions: Combine flour, salt, tartar and water in saucepan and cook for 3 to 4 minutes until it forms a ball in pan.
Remove from heat. Knead in oil and coloring.
Store in covered container.
Enjoy.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, salt and eggs.
Add cold and boiling water, 2 cups flour and yeast mixture.
Beat well.
Gradually add remaining flour until well mixed.
Cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate and use as needed.
Shape and let rise.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Rub butter or margarine over rolls as soon as they are out of the oven.
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: chinese chicken salad dressing
directions: Mix well.
Toss with Chinese chicken salad.

title: peasant cheese bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine flours, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cheese. In a second bowl, big enough for the purpose, combine syrup, beaten egg, and the buttermilk. Add the "wet" stuff to the "dry" ingredients. Mix just enough to thoroughly combine. Knead about 10 to 12 times on a board or flat surface that has been sprinkled with the oats. Mold into a 7-inch (17.5 cm) ball on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° (190 C) from 45 to 50 minutes or until bread sounds hollow when tapped underneath. Cool completely. Rewarm to serve.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Whip the egg whites until stiff; fold in sugar, baking powder and vanilla. Add to this mixture the cracker crumbs and nuts. Pour into a slightly greased pie plate and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool; top with small tub of Cool Whip.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Wrap chicken with bacon.
Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with mixture of sour cream and soup.
Bake uncovered for 3 hours at 275°.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 tablespoon milk.
Spread in pie crust.

title: squash balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot deep fat.
Fry to golden brown.

title: muenstrously delicious onion casserole
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan. Add onion rings. Cover and cook slowly over low heat, stirring often, for 20 to 30 minutes or until soft. Spoon into a 6-cup, fairly shallow baking dish. Spread cheese over top and sprinkle with pepper. Heat soup and milk in same frying pan in which onions were cooked, stirring until smooth. Pour over onion-cheese layer. Stir lightly with tip of knife to let sauce flow to bottom. Overlap enough bread slices, buttered side up, to make a ring around top. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bread is toasted and sauce is hot. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken spread or turkey
directions: Grind chicken in meat grinder (small holes).
Add sweet relish.
Mix well.
Add mayonnaise to make spreadable.

title: mushroom croustade
directions: Slice your bread into 2-inch slices.
Trim the crust, pull the center out of the bread, leaving the bottom intact.
You will be left with a flat bottomed "cup" of bread.
Your mushrooms will cover any imperfections.
Brush each bread croustade with a tablespoon of the melted butter.
Put into a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, watching carefully until they just turn a golden color around the edges and are slightly toasted.

title: melt in the mouth cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake for 5 minutes at 400°.
Remove from cookie sheet while warm. Cookies are paper thin and melt in your mouth!

title: white christmas chili
directions: Place chicken, 5 cups water and half of onion in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat and cook 15 to 18 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken, reserving broth in Dutch oven. Cut chicken into bite-size pieces; set aside.

title: apple cake
directions: Stir all together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: polish cookies(chris chickies)
directions: Sift flour on table.
Make a well in the middle of the flour. Put all of the ingredients except flour in mixer and beat for about 2 minutes.
Mix a small amount of mixture in center of flour until sticky.
Continue until mixture is gone.
Roll this dough paper thin.
Cut a small rectangle.
Make a slit in the middle and pull one end of rectangle through slit to look like a bow tie.
Fry in hot oil for a few seconds.
Drain on brown paper bags.
Sprinkle with 10x confectioners sugar.
(Usually made for the Christmas season.)

title: opal's sweet pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over the cucumbers and onions.
Let set for 2 hours.
Mix the sugar and vinegar.
Pour over the cucumbers and onions.
Place in bags or containers and freeze.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: To make syrup:
In a heavy skillet, melt the first cup of sugar over low heat until clear and medium brown, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; slowly add boiling water, stirring constantly.
Stir over low heat until caramelized sugar dissolves. Measure 1/2 cup syrup and set aside for icing.
Add water to remaining syrup to make 1 cup of liquid.
Cool.
Sift dry ingredients into bowl, add shortening and 2/3 cup cooled syrup. Beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining 1/3 cup syrup, eggs and vanilla. Beat 2 minutes more.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch round pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pans.

title: jambalaya
directions: Slice sausage thin and cook until brown. Remove. Place chicken in same skillet and cook until done. Remove. Saute vegetables in oil and drain. Return to pan. Add vegetables and 1 1/2 cups water for every cup of rice. Add salt. Bring to boil. Add meat. Bring to boil. Add rice and cook slowly until it is dry. Stir occasionally.

title: baked pork chops
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook
macaroni	in
boiling
water.
In small saucepan, pour milk.
Add	eggs
and heat.
Stir with fork and mix well. Add margarine, salt and pepper.
Cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Set aside.
Grate cheese.
Put a layer of macaroni,	layer of sauce and a layer of cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is light brown.

title: baked spaghetti(makes 12 servings)
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in margarine. When tender, add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano. Simmer 10 minutes. (Add beef if desired.) Place half of the spaghetti in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with half of the tomato mixture. Sprinkle with 1 cup of cheese. Repeat layers. Mix the soup and water and pour over casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.

title: fruit swirl coffee cake
directions: Blend sugar, butter, baking powder, vanilla and eggs with mixer on low speed. Scrape bowl constantly. Beat 3 minutes on high, scraping bowl constantly. Stir in flour. Spread 2/3 of the batter on a jelly roll pan. Spread pie filling over the batter. Drop remaining batter by tablespoonfuls onto pie filling. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Combine confectioners sugar and milk to make glaze. While the cake is still warm drizzle glaze on top.

title: banana gingersnaps
directions: Puree banana.
Combine flour, ginger, soda and salt.
Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in banana, molasses and lemon peel.
Beat in flour mixture.
Cover; refrigerate one hour.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with 3-inch cookie cutter.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed with cooking spray.
Prick with fork. Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over cookie tops.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes and then cool

title: oven chicken breast
directions: Mix and put over chicken breasts.
Use Reynolds Wrap in pan. Cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and put into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: chocolate peanuts
directions: Melt chocolate in
double boiler.
Add chopped peanuts; pour into peanut mold.
Place
in freezer for about 3 minutes. Pop out of mold onto wax paper.
Yields 75 peanuts.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook vermicelli (before cooking break into small pieces). Marinate with the remaining ingredients; mix with mayonnaise. Refrigerate overnight.
It keeps well.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Combine 1 Tbsp. sugar and flour and sprinkle over bottom of pie shell, set aside. In a medium sauce pan bring corn syrup, brown sugar and remaining sugar to a boil. Remove from heat, stir in butter until melted. Let cool for 3 minutes. Gradually stir in eggs into hot mixture. Add walnuts and mix well. Pour into pie shell. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Place pie in oven immediately reduce heat to 325 degrees and bake for 55 minutes, or until top is browned.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour.
After all other ingredients are combined, add flour last.
Bake at 350° in loaf pans for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: norwegian cookie cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 10 x 15-inch jelly-roll pan with 2 teaspoons butter.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in vanilla and flour.
Mix in almonds. Spread batter evenly into the pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until the surface is light gold color.
Let cool in the pan.
With a sharp knife, cut into small squares.
Makes about 2 dozen very rich buttery cookies.

title: cheese cake (low carbs)
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Add all 4 ingredients to mixing bowl and beat with mixer.
Spray small baking dish with Pam and add cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until top begins to turn a very light brown.
Garnish with chopped walnuts.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Stir together salt, sugar and vinegar until all is dissolved. Combine vinegar mixture with cucumbers, onions, pepper and pimentos.
Put into clean jars and let sit for 24 hours.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pork back ribs with sauerkraut
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook ribs a few pieces at a time, until well browned, removing pieces as they brown.
Pour off drippings from skillet.
Return ribs to skillet. Add water and salt; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in sauerkraut and brown sugar; cover and simmer 45 minutes longer, until ribs are fork-tender.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix jello as directed.
Add all other ingredients.
Set to chill, then put Cool Whip on top.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Step 1:
Mix 2 parts white glue with 1 part vinegar.

title: peach dessert
directions: Combine margarine and cake mix with a fork until it is crumbly. Spread in an 8 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Spread peaches over cake mixture.
Mix sour cream and egg yolks and spread over peaches. Sprinkle cinnamon over mixture as desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Other fruits may be used.

title: glazed corned beef
directions: Cover beef with water.
Add garlic, bay leaf and peppercorns. Cover.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 hours until tender.
Remove.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease or Pam a metal baking pan.
Roll chicken in saltine cracker crumbs.
Place chicken (i.e. breast side down, etc.) in pan.
Dab one piece of margarine on each piece of chicken.
Cook until side faced down is browned.
Turn pieces and dab more margarine on each piece.
When both sides are browned, remove from oven and saturate with one or two small cans of Carnation milk (not evaporated milk).

title: burger chili and chips
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add chili.
Mix well.
Line regular size casserole dish with Fritos.
Spoon on meat mixture. Top with cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dutch pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in skillet.
Powdered buttermilk may be used.
Egg Beaters may also be substituted for the egg.
This is a high fiber, low-fat recipe.

title: granny dusek's old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop mixture by the heaping teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until light brown.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix the butter, white sugar and brown sugar together.
Add eggs, vanilla and soda.
To this, add oats and flour.
Add potato chips and stir.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 9 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter for the filling in a saucepan.
Blend in flour. Add broth, milk and seasonings.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Heat thoroughly.

title: vanilla shake
directions: Place ice cubes in blender. Pour enough milk to cover ice cubes 3/4.
Add half and half to cover ice cubes completely.
Add ice cream.
Add vanilla.
Blend and enjoy!

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion.
Drain excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes until thickens.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a heavy 12-inch skillet, brown the chicken in hot oil on all sides.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add mushrooms (if using fresh), sweet peppers, onion and garlic to skillet drippings. Cook until the vegetables are tender.
Add mushrooms (if using canned), wine and red pepper to vegetable mixture.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until almost all liquid evaporates.
Add undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, lemon juice, basil, sugar, thyme, salt and pepper.
Return chicken to pan.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes until chicken is tender or bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over the cooked pasta.

title: piragi(aka: latvian ham crescents)
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Warm milk, butter and salt together and add to the yeast mixture.
Add sugar, eggs and flour.
Knead until soft and elastic.
Let rise once (30 to 45 minutes).
Flatten dough and divide into walnut-sized pieces. Shape each piece into a flat rectangle.
Place a heaping teaspoon of filling in the middle; fold over.
Pinch edges together, forming a crescent.
Place each piece, seam side down, on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise for about 15 minutes.
Brush with raw whipped egg and bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes, until light golden brown.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute beef, pepper, onion and celery about 10 minutes. Pour into large, greased casserole.
Drain corn and spoon over top.
Last spoon mashed potatoes evenly over all.
Bake in a 325° oven about 30 minutes or until brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: corn pudding supreme
directions: Mix creamed corn, egg, sugar, flour and nutmeg until blended. Add cream and fold in frozen corn.
Pour into a greased baking dish and dot with the butter and bake at 300° until corn pudding is thick, about an hour.

title: cinnamon jello
directions: Dissolve candies in 2 cups boiling water.
Add to jello and add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
When jello is partially set, add apples, celery and nuts.

title: seafood salad dip
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add heated soup. Add softened cream cheese. Mix until thoroughly blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in mold and chill.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix
all
the ingredients and store in tight container. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: my mama's chocolate pie
directions: Cook 2 cups sugar, cocoa, flour, Pet milk, egg yolks and salt on top
of
stove
at
medium
heat
until mixture becomes thick. Then add vanilla and butter.
Pour into 2 precooked pie shells.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, water and ReaLemon juice.
Over high heat, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cook and stir until slightly thickened and clear, 4 to 5 minutes. Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature. Stir in strawberries; turn into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 4 to 6 hours, or until set.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes one 9-inch pie.
