title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugars until smooth. Add egg; mix thoroughly.
Mix in water and vanilla.
Mix together flour, cinnamon and baking soda; add to egg mixture and mix well. Mix in oats and raisins.
Bake on cookie sheet for 15 to 18 minutes, until edges are done, but centers are still soft.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch glass baking pan, dilute soup and wine; stir with fork.
Place chicken breast on top of soup.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Cover with stuffing mix and dab margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn from cob. Chop peppers, cabbage and onions. Mix thoroughly. Heat 2 cups vinegar to boiling; add sugar, salt, mustard, flour and turmeric, which had been combined with 2 cups cold vinegar. Heat to boiling. Stir constantly until slightly thickened. Add chopped vegetables including the corn. Stir until well blended. Cook slowly for about 30 minutes. Put into pint jars and seal.

title: old-fashioned rice pudding
directions: In heavy saucepan, bring milk and salt to simmer.
Stir in rice and simmer 15 minutes stirring occasionally.
Add raisins and cook until rice is tender, about 5 minutes.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs with sugar, vanilla and evaporated milk.
Add 1 cup cooked rice mixture; stir until blended.
Return mixture to saucepan and cook over low heat stirring occasionally until slightly thickened, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour into bowl and cool, stirring frequently.
Serve warm or well chilled with sprinkle of nutmeg.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well and form into a loaf.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Top with additional ketchup after 30 minutes of baking.
Return to oven and continue baking.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, margarine, salad oil, eggs and extract.
Add flour, cream of tartar and soda.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten cookies with flat end of glass. Dip flat end in sugar, then flatten cookies one at a time.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Grate rind from lemon; place in container of blender.
Peel and discard outer white skin from lemon.
Cut lemon into small chunks, removing seeds.
Place lemon in blender.
Cut butter into small chunks.
Place butter, eggs and sugar in blender.
Process just until smooth.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set; cool before serving.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Whip cream.
Add cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Blend.
Add all the remaining ingredients.
Fold and freeze in cylindrical containers or empty frozen juice containers.
Lasts well for two weeks.
Serves 6-8.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine soup, sour cream and garlic salt. Add potatoes and Cheddar cheese, mix well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350 for 55-60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Bake half hour at 350° to 400°.

title: upside-down peach cake
directions: Drain peaches; reserve 1/3 cup liquid.
Melt margarine in a 9-inch round cake pan.
Stir in brown sugar and water.
Arrange peaches and cherries in pan.
Spoon upside-down cake batter over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack 5 minutes. Loosen sides; invert onto plate.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tasty caesar salad
directions: Combine olive oil and garlic cloves in a small bowl.
Allow this mixture to stand 4 hours, stirring occasionally before removing and discarding the garlic.
Arrange romaine and croutons in a salad bowl.
In separate bowl, combine garlic, oil, dressings, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, eggs and pepper; stir briskly.
Pour this dressing over salad; toss well while mixing in Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Bake at 450° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter sugarless cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Cream together margarine, sugar, peanut butter, orange zest and vanilla. Add egg, orange juice and sweetener. Blend well. Add dry ingredients gradually; mix well after each addition. Measure 1 level tablespoon dough for each cookie. Roll in hands to form ball. Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork. Bake about 15 minutes. Store cookies in a tightly covered tin.
These cookies have better flavor and texture 24 hours after baking.

title: bacon water chestnuts
directions: Wrap each chestnut with a 1/2 slice bacon.
Secure with a toothpick.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake uncovered for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Drain grease off.
Mix sugar and catsup.
Pour over bacon and cover with foil.
Bake another half hour or so.
Serve hot.

title: yummy torte
directions: Cut butter into flour, blend well and add pecans.
Press into bottom of 9 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Watch closely.
Cool.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch layer pans (you may use only 2 layers if you wish, baking time will be slightly longer.
Heat chocolate and water on top of stove in a medium saucepan, stirring constantly until chocolate is completely melted.
Mix flour with baking soda and salt; set aside.
Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition until smooth.
Beat egg whites until they form stiff peaks.
Gently stir into batter.

title: mississippi sin
directions: Slice bread lengthwise and hollow out. Mix other ingredients together and spoon into bread shell. Replace top of loaf, wrap in foil and bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: meat-za-pie
directions: Mix in bowl with fork the ground meat, crumbs, milk and garlic salt.
Press in 9-inch pie pan, bottom and edges.
Spread tomato paste or catsup over meat.
Add mushrooms on top.
Top with shredded cheese; sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Pound each breast to 1/4-inch thickness with a meat mallet. Coat each piece of chicken in flour.
Saute the chicken in oil over medium heat in a 10-inch frying pan for 2 1/2 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken from pan and drain on brown paper.
Add onion to pan and saute 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Pour off excess oil from the pan.
Return chicken and onion to pan. Mix bouillon and hot water; pour over chicken.
Pour lemon juice over chicken.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put into greased
casserole. Bake approximately 45 minutes in 350° oven. Sprinkle cheese over top 5 minutes before removing from oven. Serves 8.

title: rum punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl. Add large block of ice and decorate with fruit.

title: pineapple-pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool cake completely.
Make pudding according to package.
Spread over cool cake.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Spread well drained pineapple on top of pudding.
Spread Cool Whip over the top.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Can sprinkle top with chopped nuts if desired.
Good cake for summer picnics.

title: french fried onions
directions: Peel onions under water.
Slice in bowl of milk; let stand 15 minutes.
Drain and dry with towel.
Beat eggs; add salt, butter, milk and flour to make smooth batter.
Drop onions into batter and drop them into hot fat.

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: In skillet over medium heat, melt margarine.
Cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Spoon off fat.

title: party favorite
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine all ingredients.
Serve at your next party.

title: sugar-free banana split cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Beat next 3 ingredients until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon over cooled crust. Top with sliced bananas, pineapple and mixed vanilla pudding. Spread over bananas and pineapple.
Top with whipped cream.
Can add nuts and cherries on top.

title: oreo creme pie
directions: Chop 10 cookies; set aside.
Finely roll 26 cookies.
Combine crumbs and margarine, press evenly into 9-inch pie plate. chill while preparing filling.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef cubes.
Add everything to crock-pot.
Cook on low all day.
Season to taste.

title: german chocolate pudding
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together; add chocolate mixture to beaten egg yolks, then add 2/3 cup of the powdered sugar.
Chill, then fold in whipped cream.
Beat egg whites until they begin to stand up in peaks; add remainder of sugar (1/3 cup) to egg whites and fold into chocolate mixture.
Grind vanilla wafers and line a 9 x 9-inch deep dish with part of the crumbs.
Spread 2 cups of chocolate mixture over the crumbs.
Repeat until mixture is used. Top pudding with crumbs.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Cut in 3 x 3-inch pieces.
Makes 9 servings.

title: baked apple
directions: You will need measuring spoons, paring knife and a ramekin dish.

title: parmesan scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a small bowl.
Set seasoning mixture aside.
Use a glass casserole.
Layer 1/3 of potatoes in a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch casserole.
Sprinkle 1/2 of seasoning over potatoes.
Repeat layers with remaining potatoes and seasonings; end with potatoes.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Combine whipping cream and water.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover and bake 30 minutes.
Let stand before serving for 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 guests.
Very good.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze water from chopped spinach.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve as a dip with raw vegetables: carrots, celery, broccoli, etc.

title: brownie cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a mixing bowl; stir until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan completely.
Spread Chocolate Frosting over top; cut into squares. Yield:
2 dozen.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: Microwave on High the whole squash until soft, 8 to 10 minutes.
When cool, cut open and remove seeds and pulp.
Scoop squash away from skin; set aside.
Saute onion, leek and celery in large soup pot with margarine.
Add water, bouillon, squash, cream (or milk) and spices.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
(Squash can be substituted with pumpkin.)

title: cream chicken breasts with french onion rice
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch dish and put chicken in single layer. Place sliced cheese on top of chicken.
Mix chicken soup and water and spread on top of cheese.
Top with stuffing.
Pour melted butter or margarine over the
top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and trim squash.
Cover with water; boil until done.
Add onion.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then flour.
Melt butter in nonstick skillet.
Brown chicken over medium heat.
Stir in soup mix blended with water.
Put lemon slices on chicken.
Bring it to boil, then simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Check if chicken is done.
Serve meal with hot white rice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix thoroughly by hand.
Shape into small balls.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.
Serve warm.

title: our favorite chicken casserole
directions: Cook the chicken until tender; remove from stock and cool. Drain the stock to remove any bones or chicken pieces, saving the stock. Cook noodles in stock until tender.
Drain. While chicken in cooking, saute celery, onion and green pepper in margarine in microwave until tender. Cream the soups together and add to noodles. Bone the entire chicken and
fold into noodle mixture. Stir in the cheese, mushrooms and sauteed vegetables.
Fold peas and juice in gently. If you have Dutch rusk, crumble on top or use fine cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until bubbly.
(If using 16 ounces of noodles, you may wish to add 1 more can of soup for moisture.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, evaporated milk and margarine to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Take off heat. Add peanut butter chips, Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, strawberry gelatin, water and vegetable oil well.
Add eggs; drain strawberries and add.
Cook in oiled and floured pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: fruit dip from heaven
directions: Cut up favorite fresh fruit of your choice.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill 4 hours.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add milk and flour alternately. Beat all together for about 2 minutes.
Add flavoring and coconut. Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until knife comes out clean.
Check closely.

title: ambrosia parfaits
directions: Combine oranges, pineapple and banana.
Mix coconut with cereal.
In 2 dessert glasses layer fruit, coconut, yogurt, fruit, coconut, yogurt, coconut.
Top each with one mandarin orange.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Spread pineapple evenly over bottom and into corner of pan.
Spoon in pie filling. Spread evenly.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Sprinkle nuts evenly over cake.

title: pastry wrapped baked brie
directions: Have a cookie sheet ready.
Lightly dust work surface with flour.
Unfold and roll 1 sheet of puff pastry to an 11-inch square.
Transfer pastry to cookie sheet.
Center Brie on pastry. Brush beaten egg in a 1-inch border around Brie.
Repeat pastry instructions for second sheet and place over Brie to cover it. Smooth pastry over top and side of Brie.
Press to egg-brushed border to seal.
Trim to within 1/2-inch around Brie with sharp knife.
Crimp border with a fork.
Brush all over with egg. Freeze on cookie sheet until hard.
Remove from sheet and wrap in plastic or foil wrap; return to freezer.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and cool.
Add celery, carrot and onion. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over macaroni mixture. Chill.

title: olive-nut bread
directions: Measure mix into large bowl.
Add sugar.
Beat egg and add with milk.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts and olives. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread thin layer of cream cheese on ham slices.
Place pickle spear on one edge.
Roll up tightly and place on cookie sheet. Freeze.
Slice in thin slices while still frozen.
Serve thawed.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder and soda together.
Cover each piece of chicken with this mixture.
Fry to a golden brown.
Place on a paper towel.

title: teacakes
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Mix cream cheese and Dream Whip together.
In pan, put layer crackers and butter, then a layer of Dream Whip and cheese, then a layer of cherries, then layer of Dream Whip and cheese and then another layer of crackers and butter.
Chill and serve.

title: dutch green beans
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces.
Cook until crisp and drain. Cook onion in small amount
of
bacon
fat
until
clear.
Add cooked beans, vinegar and	seasoning.
Heat
until
hot.
Turn into serving dish. Garnish with crisp bacon. Serves 8.

title: bell pepper roast
directions: Mix and bake in moderate oven approximately 45 minutes.
Pour gravy over.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Spray inside of a large brown paper grocery bag liberally with Pam-type cooking spray.
Add popped popcorn.
In medium saucepan, bring to a boil the brown sugar, corn syrup and margarine.
Cook about 6 minutes.
Add baking soda; mixture will foam up.
Pour over popcorn in bag and shake.
Microwave 1 minute and 30 seconds and shake bag.
Repeat.
Microwave 30 seconds and shake.
Repeat. Cool.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together with spoon the mayonnaise, sugar and cheese. Layer other ingredients in a large bowl in this order: lettuce, cauliflower, onion, crumbled bacon and dressing mixture; spread on top.
Cover and let set overnight.
Mix salad before serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Put sugar and gelatin in blender.
Process on low until well mixed.
Add boiling water and run on low until gelatin is dissolved.
Add egg yolks; run on high until smooth.
Add peanut butter and run on low until smooth.
Pour into bowl.
Chill until slightly thickened.

title: old fashioned corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat egg whites separately. Bake until brown in 300° oven.
May be made in advance.

title: danish potato salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; gradually beat in well beaten eggs.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Beat in salad dressing.
Toss together remaining ingredients.
Pour on dressing; toss gently.
Adjust seasoning, if necessary. Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put flour, salt and pepper in a bowl. Cut in butter and rub in flour with fingers until mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs.
Using table knife, mix cheese, mustard, egg yolk and then gradually add 2 tablespoons cold water until stiff dough forms.
Knead lightly on a floured surface.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut into 1/4-inch x 2 x 5-inch strips.
Place on greased baking tray, twisting strips.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: south of the border chicken
directions: In a skillet in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides. Remove.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice and sugar.
Add pineapple juice and chill. Pour into punch bowl and add chilled ginger ale when ready to serve.
Makes 32 punch cups.

title: harold's barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions until tender.
Mix all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour, or until sauce thickens.
Sauce will stay on meat when served.
Use as a table sauce after meat is cooked.

title: chicken salad
directions: Drain mushrooms and combine with chicken, celery, pecans and bacon in a large bowl.
Blend mayonnaise with remaining ingredients and add to chicken mixture, tossing lightly. Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together.
Pour in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: lasagna
directions: Combine ground beef, garlic, onion soup, water, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt, oregano and sugar.
Simmer sauce for 30 minutes.
Boil lasagna noodles (put 2 tablespoons oil in water). Drain water.
Layer ingredients in a baking dish, sauce, noodles and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers until dish is full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pumpkin cake
directions: Thoroughly grease a 3-quart fluted tube pan; sprinkle with bread crumbs and set aside.
Mix well the flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices.
Set aside.
In large bowl, cream butter with sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in half the flour mixture, then the pumpkin and remaining flour mixture just until well blended.
Stir in walnuts.

title: low-fat taco meat
directions: In a 2-quart measuring cup or Pyrex bowl, put a plastic strainer.
Put the ground beef in the strainer.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir and cook again until meat is done.
All fat will be drained off the meat as you lift the strainer out of the bowl or measuring cup.
Put ground beef in a serving bowl and add taco seasoning.
Follow microwave directions on the package. Enjoy greaseless taco meat.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Shred or slice enough cabbage (very thin) for 4 to 6 people or as large as you want.
Cut a couple stalks of celery in very small pieces and 1/2 green pepper, cut in small pieces (optional).
Put in other vegetables that you might have on hand.
Cube tomato if desired.
Toss these together and add about a half or whole package of fake crab meat.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Combine flour, oats, sugar and cinnamon and cut in butter until crumbly.
Put apples in bottom of baking dish (8 x 8-inches) and sprinkle with topping.
Microwave on High 14 to 16 minutes. If apples are frozen, thaw and drain slightly.

title: orphan annie stew
directions: Do not brown meat.
Mix all in casserole or Dutch oven.
Bake covered at 250° for 5 hours.
(Don't peek.)

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to hot (425°).
Generously butter deep muffin cup. Beat eggs, milk, flour and salt with a rotary egg beater or mixer. Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into cups and fill half.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until puffed and brown.
Serve immediately with butter.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine
cracker
crumbs,
1/2	cup
melted
butter and sugar; mix well.	Pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: papa's potato casserole
directions: Mix all in large bowl. Melt butter, add last. Put in 8 x 11-inch glass pan. Cook at 350° for 1 hour. Save some of the cheese to place on top before putting in oven.

title: choco-chip cream cheese bars
directions: Leave rolls of chocolate chip cookies on counter for 1 hour. Press 1 roll in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over chocolate chip dough.
Cover with flattened pieces of cookie dough from 2nd package.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: smothered eggs
directions: Place 1 slice of cheese, with a hole cut
in
the center of a slice of bread.
Separate egg.
Place egg
yolk in hole of cheese. Beat egg white and spread on top of egg yolk, covering all the cheese.
Put 1/2 to 1 slice of
raw
bacon	across	the top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: wild bird treat
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Stuff in pine cones and roll in mixed seed. Hang in trees.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chop shrimp if they are large.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° until all ingredients are done or approximately 1 hour.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, add 1 1/2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 5-inch ungreased loaf dish.
Microwave on High 16 to 21 minutes, or until firm, rotating dish.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine beans, brown sugar, catsup, chopped onion and mustard in casserole dish.
Lay slices of onion and bacon across top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Add pineapple, bananas and strawberries.
Fold in cool whip.
Pour into dessert dishes and freeze.
Thaw about 30 minutes before serving.

title: stickies
directions: Spread butter on pie shell (all the way to the edge). Sprinkle on brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut into 1-inch slices.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes (until lightly browned). This is a good way to use left over pie dough after the crust is made.

title: ambrosia dessert
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid. Add cold water to liquid to measure 1 cup. Stir boiling water into Jell-O in a large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid. Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened (consistency of beaten egg whites). Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound. Stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and coconut.
Pour over graham cracker mix.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit in a large bowl.
Just before serving, add nuts and bananas.

title: reuben burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients except sauerkraut and cheese.
Shape mixture into 5 patties, about 3/4-inch thick.

title: uncooked oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk together and boil for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper and let set until firm.

title: fruit dip
directions: Add ingredients in bowl.
Beat well.
Serve with fresh fruit slices.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Fry on a greased griddle.
When it starts to bubble, turn the pancake.
Yields 6 medium pancakes.

title: cheese topped stuffed peppers
directions: In a large pot of boiling water, parboil peppers for 5 minutes.
Drain.
In a skillet, cook beef and onions until browned.
Drain.
Add rice, salt and 1 cup of tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Heat oven to 350°.
Stuff peppers with beef mixture. Place in ungreased baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over peppers.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; serve.

title: phyllis' corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet cook beef and onions until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add diced chilies and pepper. Divide beef mixture evenly on each tortilla.
Using one half cup shredded cheese, sprinkle a small amount of enchilada sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Roll each tortilla in and place in pan.
Cover with remaining cheese and sauce.
Bake 15 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.
Yields 4 portions (2 enchiladas).
Per portion:
348 mg calcium, 522 calories.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions on package.
Mash cream cheese (should be at room temperature) and mayonnaise.
Add to jello.
Mix well and put in refrigerator.
When slightly congealed, remove and add pineapple (which has been drained) and nuts.
Mix thoroughly and sprinkle marshmallows on top.
Return to refrigerator and chill until firm.

title: chicken & vegetables alfredo
directions: Prepare fettuccini according to directions.
Add frozen vegetables for last 4 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
In a skillet over medium heat, melt oleo, add chicken and cook until browned.
Add soup, milk, cheese, pepper and fettuccini mixture and cook through, stirring often.
Serves 4.

title: mommy's chocolate pie
directions: Follow directions on graham cracker crumb box for pie crust. Use a bit more crumbs and butter for thicker crust.

title: shrimp in red sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil in a large, heavy skillet over medium heat.
When onion is transparent, add tomatoes and their juice.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add vinegar, shrimp and pepper strips; stir so that all shrimp are coated with sauce. Add pepper; cover and let simmer 10 more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: sausage roll
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain on paper towels.
Roll dough out on a cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
(Spray with Pam first.) Spread about 1 tablespoon of mustard over the dough.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake as directions on package and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Prepare pudding according to package.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix Jello vanilla pudding mix with Eagle Brand milk and 3 c. sweet milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Layer Vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding.
Makes two layers.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and seasoning mix.
Layer in dish as listed.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt together in pan Hershey bars and oleo.
Mix eggs and sugar; add milk and flour alternately, then Hershey and oleo mixture, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Do not ice.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, in slow oven at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: low-fat creamy herb dressing
directions: Use hand beater.
Whip together yogurt and sour cream.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk together slowly in a large bowl. Slowly add pie filling.
Add other ingredients; mix well after each addition.
Chill before serving.

title: pineapple chicken curry
directions: Bone and slice the chicken breasts.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add strips of chicken; sprinkle with salt and cook, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper, nuts, curry and nutmeg.
Cook 2 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Add drained pineapple with 1/2 cup of syrup, water and bouillon cube. Reduce heat, cover and cook 4 minutes. Blend cornstarch with 2 tablespoons cold water.
Stir all at once into skillet.
Cook, stirring rapidly until thickened.
Serve with rice.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Whip pudding and milk.
Add powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Whip until smooth.
Blend cookies in blender until crushed.
Pour pudding into a new flowerpot.
Top with crushed Oreos.
Decorate with new flowers and gummy worms, draped over side and in and out of "dirt."
Serve with a new plastic toy shovel.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, pumpkin and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes (until golden, not brown).

title: crullers
directions: Mix together.
Drop into frying oil with spoon.
Roll in sugar.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, garlic powder, chili powder and eggs.
Break tomatoes with a fork and add to meat mixture.
Mix well.
Turn into loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Mix sugar with cranberries and let stand for 1 hour.
Add boiling water to Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Combine all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: corn fritters
directions: When you pick the corn, have a big pot of water boiling before you leave to go to the garden.
Pick the corn and run back to the house, shucking the corn as you go.
Drop the ears of corn into the boiling water and let boil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from the water, butter well, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Enjoy!

title: mint cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, Hershey's syrup, flour and vanilla.
Mix together and bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: crispy crust pizza
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving:
In medium bowl, put cornmeal and 2 cups flour.
Gradually stir in 3/4 cup cold water with fork until mixture becomes stiff and leaves side of bowl. Knead dough 2 minutes or until smooth.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and let rise 15 minutes.

title: leslie's beef brisket
directions: Put beef brisket in shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
In a separate bowl, mix beer, onion soup and cranberry sauce.
Pour over beef brisket. Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serve with mushroom rice.

title: cake doughnuts
directions: Put eggs, sugar and shortening together; mix well.
Sift together the remaining ingredients; add to the first mixture.
Mix well.
Chill dough for about 20 minutes.
Roll dough 1/2 inch onto a floured surface.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep oil.

title: mock ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: roquefort dressing(salad dressing)
directions: Crumble the cheese in small pieces and mix thoroughly with other ingredients.
Keeps in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, butter, milk and vanilla together until smooth.
Put in 2-quart buttered baking dish.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine brown sugar, Crisco, water and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Beat in eggs.
Add flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Beat at low speed until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until cookies are set. Do not overbake.
Cookies should be soft and moist.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet before removing to foil.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt together oleo and Hershey bars.
Add sugar and eggs (one at a time).
Stir in buttermilk mixture.
Add flour, flavoring and nuts.
Beat well and bake in a tube cake pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: winter delights
directions: Mix sugar and milk in a large saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla, margarine and cocoa; mix together well.
Add oats.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
They harden quickly.

title: amarette cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, then put in almond extract.
Mix and beat almonds in by hand.
Use 10x sugar as flour to make the form of small balls, then put almond half on top.
Do not use Crisco on pan, just a lot of flour.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in water in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in margarine until mixture is texture of coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: dirt
directions: Cream together cream cheese, margarine and sugar. Mix together pudding, milk and Cool Whip. Combine chocolate mixture with creamed mixture. Stir well. In flowerpot, layer mixture with crushed Oreo cookies, ending with cookies on top. Add silk flowers and plastic shovel for serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat until blended well.
Lastly, add carrots.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a 10-inch tube pan.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the pretzels, oleo, 3 tablespoons sugar and pecans.
Place in a 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Beat the cream cheese, sour cream and sugar; fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on top of pretzels and layer when cool.
Mix strawberry Jell-O in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries (do not thaw before adding), or 1 quart of fresh strawberries may be used.
After strawberries thaw in Jell-O mixture, let set until thickened. Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill; cut into squares.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In a blender
or
by
hand,
mix sugar and butter until creamy.
Add eggs,	one
at
a
time, until it's well blended. Sift flour, soda,
salt
and baking powder twice before adding to mixture.
Add a
little
at
a time to mixture until all is gone, then add the
sour	cream and flavor of your choice.
If mixture is too thick,
you	may
add
a
little milk and blend until smooth.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk; bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
(Use a timer; don't overcook.)
Stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oats; mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool, eat and enjoy!

title: fudge candy(or butterscotch)
directions: Bring sugar, evaporated milk and marshmallows to boil in deep pan at medium heat.
Boil 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add margarine, vanilla and chips.
Stir until melted.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts if desired.
Pour on buttered plate and cool before cutting into squares.

title: grilled pork loins
directions: Split loin lengthwise, but not all the way through.
Fill with sliced onions.
Pour honey over onions.
Season with seasonings. Wrap with heavy-duty foil.
Place on top rack of grill over a pan of water.
Grill 1 1/2 hours.
Split open foil.
Pour barbecue sauce over and grill for 30 minutes more.

title: easy chicken and salsa
directions: Rinse chicken breasts and place in a glass or aluminum baking pan.
Pour salsa over chicken and cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Great over rice.

title: julie's chocolate chip squares
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice 1 roll of cookie dough and 1/3 of second roll.
Arrange and pat into pan.
Beat eggs, cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Pour over cookie dough.
Slice remaining cookie dough thin and arrange on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix together by hand and press in muffin tart pan.

title: ginger lemonade
directions: Juice lemons, then strain into a pitcher.
Put ginger pieces and 2 cups of the water into a blender; process about 1 minute until the ginger is finely grated.
Strain into the pitcher, using a spoon to press out as much liquid as possible.
Add the remaining water and sugar and stir until the sugar is dissolved.

title: mother's no-knead yeast rolls
directions: Melt enough solid Crisco to yield 1/2 cup melted Crisco.
Mix salt, sugar and 1/2 cup cold water.
When Crisco is melted, add it to salt, sugar and cold water mixture (mixture may curdle; that's okay).

title: spinach dip with pumpernickel bread
directions: Chop onion fine.
Chop water chestnuts coarsely.
Thaw and drain spinach.
(Squeeze to rid of water.)
Mix ingredients together and store overnight.

title: bavarian wiener casserole
directions: Halve 4 hot dogs and reserve.
Slice remaining hot dogs 1/4-inch thick.
Mix soup and mayonnaise; add sauerkraut and hot dogs and caraway seed.
Mix together.
Add potatoes.
Top with remaining 4 hot dogs; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: diabetic coconut pie
directions: Let milk come to boil.
Add cornstarch to 1/4 cup milk and 3 egg yolks (beaten).
Thicken milk; take off stove and add coconut, oleo, vanilla and sweetener.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Make meringue with 1 package sweetener and put in oven for about 20 minutes.

title: bohemian coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Ice cake with frosting.

title: jello fingers
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve 1 large package Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Refrigerate for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ? punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/4 cups of boiling water.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: dip for chips
directions: Cut Velveeta cheese into cubes.
Cut cream cheese into cubes. Melt in microwave or low heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in canned chili and serve hot with chips.

title: old fashion pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly, then add rest of ingredients and beat. Pour into crust shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then turn temperature to 350° for 45 minutes longer, until knife comes clean out of pie.

title: chili meat loaf
directions: Drain kidney beans and mash.
Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix lightly.
Put in loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until done.

title: quick coconut icing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and chill.
After you cake is cooled, spread on cake and place in refrigerator.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: *May substitute one (8 1/2 ounce) corn muffin mix.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Add celery, onion, pepper and seasonings; cook until almost tender.
Add beans, tomato sauce and hominy.
Simmer until thick.
Put in casserole dish; bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with grated sharp Cheddar cheese and crushed tortilla chips.
Bake until cheese bubbles.
Bake at 350° to 375°. Freezes well.

title: breakfast puff
directions: Put butter in 9 x 13 glass dish (Corning works well).
Put in 450 degree oven to heat.
In blender, whip eggs then very slowly add flour and milk, alternately.
Pour into hot pan and bake for 15 minutes.
Check; if not done, bake a few more minutes.
This will puff up like a souffle.
Serve with syrup and strawberries.

title: almond crescents
directions: Cream first three ingredients and add 1 tablespoon water. Stir in flour; add nuts and mix well.
Shape in crescents and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on rack, then roll into powdered sugar.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all very well and put into a bowl.
Chill overnight.

title: pepper jelly mold
directions: With a mixer, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add jelly. Blend well.
Soften gelatin in cold milk; add boiling milk.
Stir until dissolved.
Combine with cream cheese mixture.
Pour into 3 1/2 cup mold.
Chill.
Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add all ingredients, except crackers.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in baking dish. Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: * I use 1 cup white and 1 cup brown.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water and oatmeal together.
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift and add flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add nuts and grated zucchini.
Mix.
Bake in 2 (9 x 5-inch) greased loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: onion sloppy joes
directions: In 10-inch skillet, brown ground beef over medium-high heat; drain. Stir in remaining ingredients, except hamburger buns. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 8 minutes or until mixture thickens.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour; mix well.
Add oleo, syrup and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans to cover top.
Bake at 350° for about 50 to 55 minutes.

title: lemon-cranberry congealed salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water over medium heat until berries pop (about 5 minutes).
Do not drain; set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set pineapple aside.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; turn down to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Wash and cook potatoes in water until tender.
Drain, cool and cube.
In heavy saucepan, brown diced bacon.
Add vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer on medium heat.
Set aside.
In roaster, add cubed potatoes, celery, onion, green pepper, pimentos, salt and pepper.
Pour bacon mixture over potatoes and bake, covered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: spicy walnuts
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
In a 1 1/2-2-quart bowl, combine the oil, thyme and hot sauce. Add the nuts and stir gently until the nuts are well coated with the oil and seasonings.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar and water.
Boil until dissolved.
Stir in apricot baby food and pineapple; set aside to cool.
Combine condensed milk and cream cheese; beat.
Stir into Jell-O mixture. Add nuts.
Pour into 9-cup mold or dish; let it set in refrigerator until congealed.

title: crunch pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Stir in eggs, one at a time. Beat well each time.
Add flavorings.
Add flour to batter in three parts.
Start with cold oven.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: ellen's slushy punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 4 cups boiling water; add 5 cups cold water. Set aside.
In another pan, mix 4 cups sugar and 4 more cups water. Bring to a boil.
Add sugar mixture to Jell-O mixture.
Add bottle of lemon juice concentrate and 1 large can of pineapple juice.
Mix all and freeze in milk cartons.
Take out of freezer 3 to 4 hours before use.
Add 2 quarts ginger ale to punch bowl with frozen mixture.
Serves 100.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Combine eggs and other ingredients.
Put 1/2 cup mixture in hot buttered skillet; cook until set and flip over to cook other side.
Place on Earthen Ware dish with heaping mound of rice. Serve with Chinese Brown Gravy.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Drain oranges.
Mix the fruit together.
Mix Tang, pudding mix and drained pineapple juice. Pour over fruit and chill.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Dice the cooked chicken; add the chicken to all of the other ingredients and mix well in
a large bowl.
Spread evenly in an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spicy guacamole
directions: Slice avocados in half; remove pit and scoop out pulp.
Place pulp into bowl and mash well.
Add Taco Bell brand thick-n-chunky salsa, Taco Bell brand taco sauce, scallions and tomatoes.
Stir well.
Add lemon and salt to taste.
Serve with Taco Bell brand tortilla chips.
Makes 2 1/2 cups or 6 to 8 servings.
Takes 5 minutes.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Arrange veggies in dish.
Mix marinade and pour over veggies. Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Layer dip (leave 1/2-inch around).
Spread refried beans on plate, then spread avocado dip.
Spread out salsa; sprinkle on cheese, tomatoes, onions and then olives.
Serve chilled with tortilla chips.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour together and set aside.
Mix butter, cocoa, water and shortening together in pan and bring to boil. Pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Add eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla; mix well.
Place in greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool and frost with chocolate fudge frosting.

title: cookies while you sleep
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Separate eggs.
When at room temperature, beat whites until frothy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Add salt and vanilla.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet that is covered with foil. Turn off oven and place cookies in oven for 1 to 2 hours or overnight.

title: mom's roast beef
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven; brown roast on all sides.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Add coffee, 3/4 cup water, bouillon and spices.
Cover and simmer for 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Combine flour and remaining water until smooth; stir into pan juices.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove roast and slice.
Serve with gravy.
Yields 8 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, melt peanut butter chips, butter and condensed milk. When melted, add chopped peanuts. Put mixture in a waxed paper lined 8-inch square pan. Smooth out. Let chill for 2 to 3 hours. Store refrigerated.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and slice potatoes.
Dice pickles and onion.
Dice salt pork and brown in skillet (like bacon); drain grease.
In bowl, combine potatoes, onions, pickles and salt pork.
Add beef bouillon, oil and vinegar.
Salt and pepper to taste and stir.

title: jamie and robby's french toast
directions: Mix vanilla, sugar, cinnamon, eggs and milk with a fork.
Dip one slice of bread in mixture and brown on preheated skillet. After browning on both sides, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook and dice potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients and serve.

title: chocolate peanut squares
directions: Microwave 3/4 cup margarine with 2 chocolate squares on High 1 to 2 minutes or until melted when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in crumbs, coconut and peanuts.
Press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan; chill 30 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Spread over crust; chill 30 minutes.
Microwave remaining margarine and chocolate squares on High 1 or 2 minutes or until melted when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds.
Spread over cream cheese layer; chill. Makes 3 dozen.

title: italian style zucchini
directions: Cut ends from zucchini, but do not peel.
Cook in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes.
Halve lengthwise.
Remove pulp with spoon.
Reserve shells.
Combine zucchini pulp with 1/2 cup of cheese and all other ingredients except margarine.
Mix well. Fill shells.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with a whisk beater.
Pour into one unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool; top with Cool Whip and a cherry.

title: egg brunch
directions: The night before, butter 9 x 13-inch pan and layer first 3 ingredients.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard, then pour over first 3 ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Unroll dough. Do Not cut into triangles leave in squares. Place 6 to 8 pepperoni or as many as you want in each square. Roll them up; brush with butter and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken waikiki beach
directions: Heat
oven 350°.
Coat chicken with flour.
Heat oil in large frying pan and brown chicken on all sides.
Remove to a shallow roasting pan;
arrange pieces, skin side up.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Prepare sauce.

title: classic bacon cheeseburger
directions: Mix meat with salt and pepper.
Form into 4 patties, about 3/4 inch thick.
Grill the patties over medium heat until centers are no longer pink.
Turn once halfway through grilling time. Toast rolls and top each burger with a cheese slice.
Remove from grill, top patties with 2 slices of bacon.
Garnish with your choice of toppings.

title: chicken dorito
directions: Heat first five ingredients.
Crush Doritos and place 1/2 in bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken on top.
Pour heated mixture on top of chicken.
Place remaining Doritos on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: I like baking this cake in an iron skillet.
Put skillet on eye of stove.
Turn on medium heat.
Put butter and sugar in pan, melt and cook 3 minutes.
Add drained pineapple.
Mix cake mix according to directions and pour on top of pineapple, butter and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Then flip cake out and enjoy!

title: sour cream dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours to blend flavors.
Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples, 1 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon flour, salt and cinnamon together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place 1 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon in plastic bag along with biscuits (cut in fourths).
Shake to coat.
Arrange in pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour fruit and liquid into serving dish. Sprinkle on instant pudding, then Cool Whip.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix flour with sugar.
Gradually add eggs and all milk.
Cook over hot water for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Chill thoroughly, then pour into a 1 gallon freezer. Finish filling with whole milk.
Freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Add corn, potato and milk. Heat.
Add salt and pepper.
Crumble bacon over before serving. Serves 4.

title: orange cool whip salad
directions: Halve oranges and pineapple chunks.
Pour Jell-O over and mix with cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill.
Serve over lettuce.

title: sweet potato-carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, soda, cinnamon, vanilla, salt and oil. Stir in pancake mix; add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a large Bundt pan.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar while applesauce is heating.
Pour hot applesauce over these; blend.
Sift all dry ingredients together; add.
Stir in raisins.
Bake at 350° to 375° in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Baking time may vary with temperature.
I check after 40 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for canned ham
directions: Brush on canned ham and marinate.
Cook on grill until ham is heated through.

title: beef-noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, salt and pepper.
Cook Betty Crocker Noodles Romanoff.
Combine ground beef, noodles, soup and milk in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
The last 5 minutes, add shredded cheese.

title: dried beef goulash
directions: Brown dried beef and flour in shortening.
Add onion, tomatoes and water.
Cook until a gravy is made.
Add salt and pepper. Cook macaroni in 2 quarts of boiling water to which salt and pepper have been added.
Drain.
Add to gravy mixture.

title: st. thaddeus summer tea
directions: Steep tea and mint for 10 minutes.
Mix lemonade, limeade, orange juice and sugar in gallon container.
Add tea and water to make 1 gallon.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.

title: special k bars
directions: Stir to combine sugar and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; mix well and add cereal.
Stir until evenly coated.
Press mixture firmly and evenly into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together in double boiler over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and spread over cereal mixture.
Let stand until cool and firm.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Blend all ingredients together; spread evenly in a dish. Refrigerate.
When the mixture becomes cold, it will become more firm and will be ready to eat.

title: special beef
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger; stir well.
Add beef, toss and set aside to marinate while preparing vegetables.
Heat oil in large pan or wok, very hot.
Add beef, toss over high heat until browned and tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn heat down and add onion, pepper, celery, broccoli and water chestnuts.
Cook while tossing until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 10 minutes. Add remaining vegetables.
Mix cornstarch with water and add to pan.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: topping for pies(replaces cool whip)
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth, then add Dream Whip.

title: quicky cake
directions: Slice cake horizontally into three layers.
Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Ice between cake layers with mixture.
Pour pie filling over cake.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Mix soup and sour cream; cut up boiled chicken into chunks and add to mix.
Crush 3 packages of crackers, then pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter; pour onto cracker crumbs.
Mix with fork and press a layer into bottom and sides of pan.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and let cool for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: dawson's famous peanut butter chiffon pie *
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Combine beaten egg yolks, 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 cup water and salt in top of double boiler.
Blend; add gelatin.
Place over boiling water, beating constantly with rotary beater until thick and fluffy.
Cool.

title: mace cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour sifted with ground mace.
Add vanilla and salt.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour at 340°.
Good plain or with "Betty's Frosting."

title: spinach leek dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Chill.
Great on crackers with raw vegetables or baked potatoes.

title: jane's rice krispie cookies(no cholesterol)
directions: Cream together sugars, salt, soda, cream of tartar, vanilla and margarine.
Add flour to creamed ingredients; mix well.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Watch for light color. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: rolled oats hamburgers
directions: Mix well and make into patties.
Handle lightly.
Brown on both sides in Pam-sprayed frying pan.
Place in casserole and pour brown gravy over patties.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: sparkling red velvet punch
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Cool.
Add the rest of the ingredients and serve.
Makes a large batch.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven 400°.
Cover bottom of 8 x 2-inch iron skillet with oil.
Set on stove burner and get smoking hot.
Put dry ingredients into a small bowl.
Add egg and oil, stir well; pour into hot skillet with oil.
Place in oven.
Bake 15 minutes.
No real southerner would use sugar in cornbread but some prefer it.

title: monkey bread
directions: Bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuit pieces.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not cut.
Pull apart with 2 forks or by hand.
In between layers, you can put nuts, apples or raisins, etc.

title: paul bunyan's chili
directions: In large skillet or Dutch oven, saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until tender.
Add ground beef and brown; drain off fat.
Drain kidney beans and reserve syrup.
Add beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings to beef mixture.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Add reserved bean liquid, if mixture becomes dry.

title: sweet tomato chowder
directions: Peel and slice tomatoes and onions. Add salt and let stand several hours. Drain, and add white vinegar. Simmer 2-3 hours, and when nearly thick, add brown sugar and mustard seed. Can while hot.

title: nita's original dessert
directions: Let your imagination run wild!

title: teriyaki seafood kabobs
directions: Cut salmon lengthwise into thin strips; cut strips into 36 (4-inch) pieces.
Wrap salmon pieces around scallops; thread 2 to 3 onto bamboo skewers.
Place kabobs in a shallow dish.
Combine soy sauce and next 3 ingredients in bowl and pour over kabobs. Cover and refrigerate.
Marinate for 30 minutes.
Roast on rack or grill 4 to 5 inches from heat approximately 4 minutes, basting with reserved marinade.

title: bayou salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except lettuce leaves, in a large bowl.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 6.

title: miami orange chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Place in flat baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread orange marmalade on each chicken breast.
Top with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Let sauerkraut and sugar sit 20 minutes.
Add celery, onion, green peppers and carrots.
Mix well with sauerkraut.
Chill and serve.
Keeps well in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: rhubarb shortcake
directions: Place cut rhubarb in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and marshmallows.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, 1 cup sugar and nutmeg or cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients and beat 1 minute.
Spread over rhubarb and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: shrimp gumbo(300 servings)
directions: Boil shrimp in 18 gallons of water with lemons and shrimp boil (in bags).
Drain shrimp; reserve 9 gallons of stock.
Brown 2 pounds flour slowly in 4 pounds oleo or other fat.
Add onions, celery and green peppers; saute until limp.
Add shrimp stock, salt, pepper, tomatoes, okra, parsley and garlic.
Cook slowly for 1 hour, then add shrimp and hot sauce.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add file powder to taste at end of cooking.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
Thicken, if necessary.
Cook rice according to package directions.

title: tempura batter
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs.
Add water to make a batter of medium thick consistency.
Good for fish and vegetables.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Brown the chicken in oil. Remove from pan, then sauce the pepper, onion and garlic.
Put chicken back in pan with seasoning. Add the tomato sauce and chili powder. Simmer about 20 minutes until done.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° for glass dish.
Microwave chocolate and butter on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended.
Mix eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and walnuts until blended.
Spread in dish.
Bake 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Break up Crisco.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into little balls and press flat with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken (or veal)
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Flatten chicken breast; season with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Mix Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs in a shallow dish.
Dip chicken in melted margarine, then roll in bread crumbs and cheese mixture. Place in baking dish.
Press leftover crumb and cheese mixture onto each piece of chicken.
Pour leftover margarine around chicken.
Bake about 25 to 30 minutes being careful not to burn. Edges will be brown.
Pour 1 can tomato sauce around chicken. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon oregano over it and make 4 balls of Mozzarella cheese; place 1 on each piece of chicken.
Pour last can of tomato sauce on chicken and cheese balls; sprinkle with last tablespoon of oregano.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes or until tender.
Serve sauce over spaghetti noodles and with a green salad.
Leftovers are great as subs.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place half of onions in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with half of crackers and half of Parmesan cheese.
Repeat with remaining ingredients (except margarine).

title: scones
directions: Rub margarine into flour.
Mix in sugar.
Put beaten eggs into milk; mix all together.
Knead slightly; roll out about 3/4 inch thick.
Cut into rounds.
Place on baking sheet; well apart.
Brush tops with a little beaten egg.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 5 to 10 minutes or until when tapped they sound hollow.
If desired, before baking, add currants, raisins, cherries or any dried fruit. Serve warm and covered in butter and jam or just plain.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts about 45 minutes or until done. If breasts are large, cut in half. sprinkle with Season-All and lemon pepper (or your favorite seasoning). Wrap each breast in a crescent roll. Place in greased 9 x 13 dish. Mix soup, sour cream, cheese and butter; heat slowly until hot and cheese melts. Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all together and chill.
Makes a large bowl full.

title: kentucky pie
directions: d surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Fit into 9-inch pie plate; trim and flute edge.
Pierce bottom with fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until bottom is cooked through but not brown.
Cool. Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Put butter and eggs into large bowl; stir in dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips; pour into cooled pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes, until top is golden.
Cool slightly on rack.
Serve warm, cut in wedges topped with Cool Whip.

title: "snow" ice cream
directions: Blend together milk, egg, sugar and vanilla.
Add clean, crushed ice until the mixture is absorbed.
Then serve in an ice cream cone, topped off with maple syrup or thawed orange juice concentrate.

title: ann trice ice cream
directions: Mix well, then use an ice cream maker (hand or electric ice cream freezer).

title: copper pennies salad
directions: Drain carrots and pour into large bowl.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour over carrot mixture.
Mix well and refrigerate.
The longer it marinates, the better it is!

title: chicken tortellini soup
directions: Combine chicken broth, vinegar, soy sauce and ginger in saucepan.
Bring to a simmer.
Add tortellini and bok choy stems; simmer 15 minutes, removing tortellini after it tests done.
Add bok choy leaves, chicken and onions.
Cook just until bok choy leaves wilt.
Return tortellini to soup.

title: cookies (from cake mix)
directions: Mix well and drop by teaspoon, 2 inches apart, on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat in oil; add onion, green pepper, garlic, celery and V-8 juice.
Simmer about 3 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Boil noodles in salt water until tender.
Grate cheese, saving some to put on top later.
Add cheese to noodles while hot, then add this to meat mixture.
Pour in casserole dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Warm in oven about 20 minutes.

title: pears with almond topping(light swedish dessert)
directions: Cut pears or apples into halves; pare and core.
Simmer for about 6 minutes in water and 1 cup sugar.
Place on a serving dish.

title: puffs
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg and enough milk to make a thick batter.
Add melted butter; drop by spoonfuls into boiling hot shortening.
Cook until brown and done in center. Serve hot, sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Serves 6 - maybe! Delicious for Sunday breakfast.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake in Bundt/tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix all together.
Can be served just plain with cracker or can be chilled, rolled and formed into a ball and rolled in parsley.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add tomato sauce and other ingredients.
Blend.
Pour into molds or dish.
Chill until firm.

title: microwave herbed chicken breast
directions: Put butter in 2-quart dish.
Microwave on Roast 1 1/2 minutes. Add seasonings to butter and mix well.
Roll chicken in butter; place skin side down.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Turn chicken and pour water or wine on chicken. Cook on High 6 to 8 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: fish chowder
directions: Fry out pork cubes until lightly browned.
Remove cubes to paper towel.
Fry onion in same pan without removing any liquid, until golden brown.
Add small amount of water; add fish.
Cook until fish is done.
Cook potatoes in separate pan; drain almost all of the water and add cooked fish and onion to potatoes.
Add pepper and milk.
You may add salt if desired before serving.

title: creamy green chile soup
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine onion, celery, garlic and margarine and cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add flour; stir well.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water.
Gradually add bouillon, milk, chili powder and pepper to mixture and stir well. Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring every 3 minutes.
Stir in chiles and microwave on High for 1 minute.
Stir well before serving.

title: lattice top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, chicken, vegetables and onions with 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar.
Bake covered at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven.
Arrange crescent rolls on top. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake uncovered until brown.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice; do not overcook.
Fry onion in oleo until tender on low heat.
Add eggs and mix.
Add rice and mix well.
Combine soy sauce with water.
Add to rice mixture.
Sprinkle just a little garlic powder.
Cover until ready to serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add all ingredients to Jell-O and mold.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt into large bowl.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Stir egg with orange rind and orange juice, then blend mixture into flour mixture.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Fold in raisins, cranberries and nuts. Spoon into greased 9 1/2 x 5 1/4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes, or until tester inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes, then invert onto wire rack.
Turn right side up.
Cool.
Wrap for 24 hours before serving.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into greased baking pan.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sugar plum squares
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed cereal over butter, then layer alternately all ingredients over top, except milk.
Pour milk evenly over top.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 25 minutes.
Refrigerate until set and cut into squares.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Blend condensed milk and lemon juice until thick.
Add peaches, pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Blend in Cool Whip. Pour into 2 small graham cracker crusts.
Chill.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and water in heavy saucepan.
Bring slowly to 230° or until syrup spins a thread.
Add peanuts and continue to cook to 300°.
Stir to prevent burning.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla, soda and salt and stir until blended. Pour into well buttered cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: noodles for noodle cutter
directions: Mix together and separate into 5 cakes.
Run through cutter on #5 setting; cut in half and run through on #3 setting.
Use scissors to cut into length of noodle you want and run through cutter.
Put cut noodles on cookie sheet and freeze immediately. When frozen, bag and keep frozen until ready to use.
When ready to use, put frozen noodles into boiling broth and cook for about 20 minutes.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Heat butter until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Remove and stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole or oblong baking dish.
Cook, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onions in butter until golden brown.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt with meat and brown.
Add soups.
Simmer, uncovered, until done.
Add sour cream and simmer a little longer. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chinese salad
directions: Drain all vegetables well.
Combine with vinegar and sugar in bowl; mix well.
Chill overnight.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: *Dissolve the cornstarch in the 1/4 cup water before adding to mixture.

title: roasted lemon-thyme potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Spray square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix oil, lemon juice and thyme in medium bowl; toss with potatoes.
Place potatoes in pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, if desired. Bake 20 minutes; turn potatoes. Bake about 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender and light brown.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix all ingredients until mixture is smooth.
Spread on cake when cool.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Blend cream, fat, salt, pepper and celery salt to make white sauce.
Combine chicken, onion juice, lemon juice and parsley. Add to sauce.
Cool; shape into balls or cones.
Dip in egg.
Roll in crumbs.
Fry in deep fat until well browned.
Serve with green peas.

title: poached fish with caper sauce
directions: *Fish you can use:
halibut, salmon, sea bass, shark, swordfish, tuna or whitefish.

title: baked potatoes with cheese
directions: Grease baking dish.
Place potatoes in dish. Pour milk over. Dot with butter.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Uncover and put cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes more, uncovered.

title: potatoes royale
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
Refrigerate.
When potatoes are cold, take skins off and grate.
Mix remaining ingredients with potatoes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: homemade hot tamales
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix with hands meal, flour and salt to taste.
Add shortening with very hot water.
Mix with hands until you can pat out.

title: hot swiss cheese dip
directions: About 1 hour before serving, mix cheese, onion and Hellmann's together.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (until golden brown and bubbly).
Serve hot with Fritos scooping chips.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix ground beef and soup together.
Spread in bottom of pie crust.
Put layer of vegetables on meat mixture.
Cover with mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Slice into pie shaped pieces and serve.

title: puppy chow or snow drops
directions: Mix together and melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Add Crispix and stir to coat.
Place in large resealable container and add confectioners sugar.
Seal container and shake until coated.
Cool.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Use any other canned fruit if desired.
Peel and grind apples, tomatoes and suet.
Mix ingredients together.
Heat to rapid boil and simmer until thick.
Pour into clean jars.
Process in boiling water for 25 minutes.

title: chile
directions: Brown hamburg; drain.
Add chopped onions and pepper.
Saute for a few more minutes to cook onions and pepper.
Add chili powder.
Add can of tomatoes to heat for about 5 to 10 minutes. Add kidney beans last and heat, stirring gently.
Serve with cheese sprinkled on top and Doritos served on side of plate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine; saute onion and mushrooms.
Add soup, cheez whiz and milk.
Mix well and heat until cheez whiz is melted.
Add broccoli and rice; pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees about 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: penne pasta casserole
directions: Cook pasta; rinse and set aside.
Saute vegetables in lots of garlic and a little olive oil.
When just tender, add pesto and mix well.
Then mix vegetables, pasta and Ricotta together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until hot throughout and cheese is melted.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain and place by layers in baking dish the following: squash, chopped tomatoes, chopped onions and green pepper (if you like).
Add grated cheeses.
Mix together the egg, melted butter and a few drops of Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over Squash Casserole and bake 20 minutes.

title: brown sugar ice cream
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 5-quart freezer. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Let set 1 hour. Yields about 1 gallon.

title: spinach vegetable dip
directions: Saute onions in butter until slightly browned, stirring frequently. Add broths and seasonings. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. Add sherry; return to a boil.
Remove from heat. Cool, skim fat, remove bay leaf and refrigerate until needed.

title: piquant orange glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients in small saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat.
Remove from heat, brush on meat the last 20 minutes of baking.

title: poor boy cake
directions: Beat all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is a chewy cake.

title: gooey butter
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat into the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread nuts over this.
Combine powdered sugar, butter, egg and cream cheese; beat well.
Spread over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: In skillet that has lid, fry bacon 2 minutes.
Stir in onions and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add hamburg and brown lightly. Stir in seasonings, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer about 25 minutes.
Stir in ripe olives.
Break 1/2 of spaghetti into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes or longer, until brown and bubbly.

title: spanish rice with chicken
directions: Mix Rice-A-Roni as directed on box.
Let this simmer.
Brown your chicken strips.
Put into Rice-A-Roni while it simmers.
Let simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Ready to eat.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: *Colored decors, assorted candies, such as jelly beans, gumdrops, candy-coated chocolate pieces, nonpariels, black, and/or red shoestring licorice.

title: lemon lime refrigerator cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add cold water; set aside.
Mix and bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool cake 20 to 25 minutes.
Poke holes about 1 inch apart with end of wooden spoon.
Slowly pour gelatin mixture into holes. Refrigerate cake while preparing frosting.

title: cherry angel dessert
directions: Place half of cake pieces in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Reserve 1/3 cup cherry filling.
Spoon remainder over cake.
Top with remaining cake.
Combine pudding mix with sour cream.
Beat smooth.
Spoon over cake.
Chill 5 hours.
Cut in 9 squares.
Garnish with filling.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly (batter will be heavy).
Stir in apples, then nuts.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve hot or cold.
Great with whipped cream.

title: canapes
directions: Mix all ingredients with the exception of party rye.
Now spread on the party rye.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: honey's sour cream candy
directions: *To make sour cream, add lemon juice or vinegar to sweet cream.

title: chicken and spaghetti noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken first. Cook noodles in the broth or stock of chicken.
Saute onion and bell pepper. Combine all, saving 1 cup grated cheese for top of casserole or topping.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Crust:
Mix until crumbly flour, oleo, finely chopped nuts and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Spread in long pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roast 1/2 cup nuts for 10 minutes to be used for topping.

title: lasagna italian style
directions: Remove sausage meat from outer casing; chop the meat.
In large Dutch oven, over medium heat, saute sausage, beef (break up beef with wooden spoon).
Add onion and garlic, stirring frequently, until well browned, about 20 minutes.
Add sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, the basil, fennel, pepper and half of the parsley; mix well.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and 1/2 cup water, mashing tomatoes with wooden spoon.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, until thick, 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit tart
directions: Cut confectioners sugar, butter and flour with pastry blender. Press into 12 0r 14-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Beat together softened cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on the cooked crust and bake until set (10 to 15 minutes).
Allow to cool some.
Arrange fruit on top in concentric circles.
Don't use bananas.
Good ones are fresh kiwi, grapes and strawberries; and also canned pineapple, mandarin oranges and peaches, but any fruit is okay, except bananas. Combine cornstarch, sugar and juices.
