Cook and stir until thickened.
Cool and spread over fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: wally's fudge
directions: In an electric skillet, set at 350°, mix Carnation and sugar. Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add taco seasoning mix, water and simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain juice and mix with beans.
Layer beans, meat, cheeses, pepper, onion and chilies.
Cut tomato on top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Crush 22 vanilla wafers and line pie pan.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add melted chocolate and beat just to blend.
Add egg yolks and beat until a fluffy mixture.
Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into pie pan.
Crush the other 22 vanilla wafers and sprinkle over filling.
Chill overnight (nice to be able to make it the day before you serve it).
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: layered salad
directions: In large bowl, place lettuce and water chestnuts.
Top with onion, celery and peas in this order.
Cover with mayonnaise (frost as cake).
Chill overnight.
Put crumbled bacon on top, then chopped eggs.
Add sliced tomatoes until covered.
Top with cheese.
Do not toss.
When ready to serve, dig deep and get some of each layer.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: canine bones(for dogs!)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add shortening.
Mix to consistency of corn meal.
Add egg and water.
Pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut and bake.

title: clam dip
directions: Brown diced onion in oil; add garlic and brown.
Turn off stove.
Add 3 cans of clams (2 with juice and 1 without).
Add lemon juice, parsley, oregano and bread crumbs.
Mix together; put into a casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together sugar and syrup in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts; microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes, until light brown.
Add margarine and vanilla; stir well.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together flour, oats and sugar in large bowl.
Stir in butter with fork to make a crumbly mixture.
Set aside.

title: baked chicken
directions: Combine celery soup, mushroom soup, milk and rice.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange chicken pieces on top.
Shake onion soup mix in package and sprinkle over chicken. Bake, covered, in 325° oven about 2 hours.

title: fluffy pineapple dessert
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together in a large bowl.
With beater add pineapple, marshmallows and cherries.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, according to package directions.
Mix broccoli, soup and cheese in bowl.
Spread over crushed crackers in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix melted oleo and cracker crumbs.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs and oleo for 15 minutes with mixer.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Slice bananas over mixture.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts and quartered cherries all over. Cool overnight.
Refrigerate until served.

title: hot and spicy shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato and shrimp.
Heat in chafing dish.
Add tomato and shrimp after mixture is melted and mixed well.
Yields 12 servings.

title: easter spinach pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until foaming.
Cook spinach according to package directions; turn into strainer to drain and press out liquid.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook onion in hot oil until wilted (about 5 minutes).
Stir spinach and onion into eggs with ham, Parmesan cheese, Ricotta cheese, salt and pepper.
Line a 10-inch pie plate with half of the pastry.
Add spinach mixture. Cover with remaining pastry.
Cut 6 (1-inch) vents in it.
Seal and flute edges.

title: overnight mashed potato casserole
directions: Mash hot potatoes in large mixer bowl.
Add cream cheese in small pieces and then butter.
Beat well until cheese and butter are melted and completely mixed.
Mix the eggs, milk and onions and add to the potato mixture along with the salt and pepper. Beat well until light and fluffy.
Place in greased 9-inch round casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes until lightly browned on top.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.
(This is a great holiday casserole.)

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda.
Add to above mixture and mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Pour into ungreased tube pan. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Turn off heat; leave cake in oven 5 minutes more.
Then open oven door; leave cake in oven 5 minutes more.
(Total baking time:
45 minutes.)
When cooled, sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.

title: sweet potato and pineapple casserole
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt, milk and flour together.
Add sweet potatoes, pineapple and butter.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Serves 6 to 8.

title: seafood and rice supreme
directions: In large skillet, cook onions, celery and green pepper in water until tender-crisp.
Add rice, shrimp, crab meat, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Mix well.
Turn into shallow buttered casserole or individual sea shells.
Top with buttered crackers.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant until tender.
Soak bread in milk.
Add eggplant and other ingredients to the bread mixture.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until fluffy and brown.

title: lemon-orange pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease Bundt pan or tube pan generously with Crisco. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt and put in large bowl of electric mixer. Add sugar, Crisco and buttermilk. Mix 1 minute to blend ingredients, then beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, blending on low speed. Add extracts. Spoon batter lightly into prepared pan. Bake for 1 hour. When cake is done, remove from oven and let sit for 5 minutes, then invert pan onto wax paper covered plate. Comes out easily if pan has been well-greased.

title: crock pot apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock pot.
Cook on low all day or night.
Stir occasionally.
If still lumpy, use egg beater and heat until smooth.
Put in jars.
Makes 7 half pints.

title: wonderful lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Cook noodles in large pot of boiling salt water until tender; drain; rinse.
Beat eggs in bowl and add remaining ingredients to eggs (except Mozzarella cheese); mix well.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Melt together sugar and margarine to boiling point.
Add nuts. Pour Rice Krispies in and mix.
Press 1/2 of mixture in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread ice cream over Rice Krispies.
Press remainder of Rice Krispies mixture over ice cream.
Freeze and cut into squares.

title: mother hershey's sugar cakes
directions: Cream
together
sugar, lard
and
eggs.
Add
sour
milk. Sift together flour, baking powder,
cream
of tartar, vanilla, lemon juice, nutmeg and salt and add to mixture.
Chill dough for two hours and then drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake
until
they begin to turn brown.

title: wally's dad's punch
directions: Mix all together and don't let anyone drinking it drive.

title: egg platski
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and flour and beat well until all lumps disappear.
Add milk and continue to mix.
Batter will be thin.
Put 1/4 cup batter into hot griddle.
Spread batter thinly into the pan.
Cooks quickly.
Flip and cook on the other side. Spread with jam or leave plain and roll up.
Makes about 12 platski.

title: autumn medley stew
directions: *Optional:
Add two packets low sodium chicken broth.

title: sausage dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream cheese. Mix well. (You can keep this warm in a small crock-pot.) Serve with Fritos Scoops chips or tortilla chips.

title: low-fat low sodium creamy stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes 1 hour in a preheated 400° oven.
After removing potatoes, increase oven temperature setting to 450°.
Slice potatoes lengthwise in half.
Scoop out potato; reserve shells. Combine potato, yogurt, salad dressing and onion; heat until fluffy.
Add more yogurt and dressing if needed.
Divide among reserved shells.
Place filled potato shells on baking sheet and return to oven.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple pudding
directions: Place apples in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
In a bowl mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add the unbeaten egg and mix.
Cover apples with this mixture.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° about 1/2 hour.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: oreo cookie surprise
directions: Crush large bag of Oreo cookies (put in Ziploc bag and roll with a rolling pin).
Melt margarine and mix together with Oreo cookies.
Pat into a 9 x 11 pan.
Take ice cream and let soften. Scoop it over and spread over crumb crust.	Use a small can of Hershey's chocolate (about the size of tomato paste can) and drizzle it over the ice cream.
Throw on a handful of salted peanuts.
Put in the freezer.
Just before serving, cover the top with Cool Whip and sprinkle crushed Oreo cookies over the top. This should be made in time to put in freezer several hours before serving.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in water in saucepan. Cook until thickened. Remove from heat; stir in gelatin. Cool briefly; pour over prepared strawberries. Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together flour, butter and powdered sugar with a fork until well blended.
Pat into ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until light brown.

title: turkey cranberry croissant
directions: Combine cream cheese, marmalade and pecans in a small bowl. Spread top and bottom halves of croissants with cream cheese mixture.
Layer turkey on bottom halves; spoon 2 tablespoons cranberry sauce over turkey.
Add lettuce and croissant top.

title: corn pudding(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix with wire whisk until uniform consistency.

title: buttermilk biscuits and gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Cook sausage and onion in skillet until sausage is done and onion is clear.
Remove sausage and onion.
Drain off all grease except for 2 tablespoons.
Stir in the flour and cook, stirring constantly, until medium brown in color.
Add hot milk, stirring constantly, and cook until thick. Stir in sausage and onion.
Taste gravy and season with salt and pepper (tasting until you get it to your liking).

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs.
Add flour and pineapple. Cook until it starts thickening.
Add 1 cup whipped cream after it cools.
Good on top of angel food cake.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash; add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour in greased casserole.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken 'n' biscuits
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, melt margarine.
Add carrots, onion, celery and mushrooms.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until vegetables are softened (2 to 3 minutes).
Sprinkle flour over vegetables and stir quickly to combine.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in broth.
Add remaining ingredients except biscuits and stir to combine.
Reduce heat to low and cook, stirring occasionally, as mixture thickens, about 15 minutes.
Transfer mixture to 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 425° oven until carrots are tender and crisp (10 to 15 minutes).
Arrange biscuits over chicken mixture and continue baking until biscuits are golden (10 to 15 minutes).

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with 1 teaspoon sugar and egg yolks.
Brown butter and sugar in pan until brown like light brown sugar.
Add 3 cups of milk, stirring continually.
Add about 1/2 cup of milk to cornstarch, sugar and egg mixture.
Add this to milk and browned sugar mixture after it comes to a boil.
Stir continually.
Place caramel sauce in baked pie shell and top with meringue topping.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Heat 4 tablespoons milk.
Add to sugar and butter mixture.
Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Add to mixture alternately with 1 cup milk. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Wash your chickens; put in a large pot and boil until done. Then you remove pot off stove and let cool.

In a deep baking pan, mix the peas, carrots, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, eggs, broth, melted butter and potato, mixing well, then take chicken off bones, cutting into chunks and mix in pan with other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: green tossed salad
directions: Cut and toss; season.
Add tomatoes last.

title: bev's chocolate pudding cake
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 1/4 cup cocoa, baking powder and salt. Stir in milk, butter and vanilla; beat with spoon until smooth. Pour batter into ungreased loaf pan. Mix 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle evenly over batter. Pour hot water over top. DO NOT MIX. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Let stand 15 minutes. Serve hot with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: barbara's biscuits
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in mini-muffin pans.
Do not grease tin.

title: chocolate-coke cake
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa and Coca-Cola to a boil in a large saucepan.
Combine flour, sugar and baking soda.
Combine warm margarine mixture with flour mixture.
Beat well.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla; beating well.
Add marshmallows and stir in.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
As soon as cake comes out of oven, spread on frosting.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done (may also be microwaved). Cook rice according to package. Chop onion and saute in butter. Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° until browned, about 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: nassi goreng
directions: Cook the rice according to the package directions and set aside to cool.
Heat the oil in a heavy saucepan and brown the meat quickly over high heat.
Add onions, garlic, salt, pepper and spices and saute for 5 minutes.
Add leeks and saute another 2 minutes.
Add the cold rice and cook for a few minutes over high heat, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp, ketchup or soy sauce and celery greens and heat through.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage, breaking into bits; drain well.
Set aside. Beat eggs; add milk, salt and dry mustard.
Layer bread, torn in bite size pieces, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: classic walnut pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine eggs, sugar, flour, corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; arrange walnuts on top.
Bake in oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake about 45 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, margarine and 1/4 cup powdered sugar thoroughly.
Press evenly in ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches, building up 1/2-inch edges.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients, except powdered sugar, until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake just until no indentation remains when touched in center, about 25 minutes longer.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into about 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 25 squares.

title: venison burgers in onion gravy
directions: Saute celery in butter.
Mix venison with bread, egg, water, salt and pepper.
Add celery and mix.
Make into patties and brown in pan.

title: cheddar-macaroni salad
directions: In large kettle, cook macaroni in large amount of boiling salted water until tender; drain.
Cool to room temperature.
Toss with cheese, celery, green pepper and onion.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise or salad dressing and milk; stir in relish, vinegar, mustard and salt.
Toss with macaroni mixture (salad will appear quite moist).
Cover and chill for several hours.
Serve in lettuce-lined bowl.
Garnish with green pepper rings, if desired. Makes 12 servings.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add baking powder and sugar gradually. Add vanilla and beat until very stiff.
Fold in cracker crumbs and nuts.
Pour into well-greased pie pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: caramel corn
directions: Spread popped corn in large shallow pan.
Hold in 250° oven to keep crisp.
Combine remaining ingredients except soda.
Cook at medium, stirring to dissolve sugar and prevent sticking, until a drop of the syrup forms a firm ball in a cup of water (248°). Then stir in the soda.
Pour over corn and mix well to coat evenly.
Return to oven for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Can also add nuts.
This can be frozen and served later in bags.

title: rotel tomato dip
directions: Put ingredients into a blender and blend at medium speed until well mixed.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Serve with corn chips.

title: uncle george's grilled chicken sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan; simmer for 10 minutes.
Brush on charcoal-grilled chicken every time you turn, until done.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Heat vegetable oil in deep fryer or deep saucepan to 350° on deep fat thermometer.

title: jello pie
directions: Boil water, jello and cornstarch until thickened.
Cool.
Add drained peaches.
Put into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: dorothy's eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; beat until well mixed. Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. May be prepared in advance to this point. Cover; refrigerate up to 24 hours in advance. Place in oven and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until firm to touch. Serves 12.

title: banana date cookies
directions: Mix bananas, dates and oil.
Add oats, spices, salt, nuts and vanilla.
Mix lightly.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: swiss cheese spread
directions: Mix together all ingredients except party ryes.
Spread mixture onto party ryes and broil for 2 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt butter.
Add rice and stir until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until rice is tender.
Remove bay leaf.

title: stuffed mushrooms ricotta
directions: Remove stems, wash and dry mushroom caps.
Place caps in 8-inch square baking dish.
Mix Ricotta, salt, Parmesan cheese, onion, lemon juice and paprika.
Stuff mushrooms with this mixture.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Add dry ingredients together.
Cream butter or margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add half of the flour and nut mixture.
Mix well.
Add pineapple, mixing well.
Add remaining flour and nut mixture.
Grease three 8 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Sprinkle bottoms with 1/2 tablespoon of flour mixture and add 1/3 of batter into each pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: lamb chops(afrikander)
directions: Combine tomato sauce, vinegar, onion, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and salt in a large bowl.
Marinade chops for 1 hour. Remove chops; reserve marinade.
Pat chops dry with paper towel. Panfry chops in melted butter until brown and tender.

title: 5-minute fudge
directions: Mix Carnation milk, sugar and salt together in saucepan over low heat.
Heat to boiling, cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add marshmallows, chocolate pieces, vanilla and nuts.
Stir 1 to 2 minutes or until marshmallows melt.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: grilled southwestern chicken
directions: Slightly beat chicken breasts with pronged mallet to flatten. Sprinkle with garlic powder and lemon pepper.
Marinate in salad dressing for 1 hour.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Put into a 9 x 13-inch dish, all ingredients, mixed together. Sprinkle chips or flakes on top and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Melt butter and mix with graham crackers.
Spread in bottom of pan.
Use directions on box for Dream Whip and add cream cheese. Blend.
Spread this mixture over graham cracker crust.
Then spread blueberry pie filling on top evenly. Let chill about 2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream together sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture with buttermilk and Raisin Bran. Add to the cream mixture.

title: lasagna
directions: For meat sauce, in a large saucepan, cook meat, onion, and garlic until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, basil, salt, and pepper.
Bring to boil, simmer, and cover.
Meanwhile, cook lasagna noodles according to directions.
For filling, combine egg, ricotta or cottage cheese, 1/4 c. of Parmesan cheese, and parsley flakes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Get your Mom's left over rice.
First you warm it up.
Put in the milk.
Put in remaining ingredients.
Cook until it bubbles.

title: apple fresh glazed cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and ginger in a bowl and set aside. Cream shortening, light brown sugar, egg and milk. Add apples. Add flour mixture and mix well. Add chopped walnuts. Let stand 20 minutes. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: moist 'n crispy onion chicken
directions: Place onion soup mix and bread crumbs in large plastic food bag and shake to blend.

title: italian dressing
directions: Blend or shake in a jar.
Store in a pint container in refrigerator.

title: chocolate almond rice brittle
directions: In heavy skillet, melt the butter.
Add sugar.
Stir to combine well.
Cook over low heat, stirring for 12 minutes until mixture is golden brown.
Stir in rice crisp to blend well. Immediately spread hot mixture into a lightly greased jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with the chocolate chips.
As soon as they start to melt, spread chocolate in an even layer all over the top.
Let cool slightly.
Then put in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour to cool completely.
Crack or break candy into pieces.

title: pepperoni pizza rolls
directions: Coat baking sheet with cooking spray. On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 12-inch square. Place pepperoni on dough, leaving 1/2-inch border around edges. Sprinkle with cheese. Roll up dough, pinching to seal seam. Trim ends to make even. Cut dough into 1/2-inch thick slices. Place on baking sheet(s) 2-inches apart. Coat pieces of plastic wrap large enough to cover sheet(s) with cooking spray. Place coated side down over rolls. Let rise in a warm place until slightly risen, 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add all ingredients and mix well.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in a pan. Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in a large bowl.
Stir carefully until all is coated.
Put sugar in
a large paper bag. Add cereal. Shake until cereal is coated. Spread out on waxed paper to set and cool. Store in covered container.

title: homemade chocolate cake
directions: Combine butter, cocoa, oil, flour, salt, sugar and eggs in pan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Then mix the buttermilk, soda and vanilla with above mixture. Pour in pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake pulls away from side of pan.

title: crab cakes
directions: Peel, wash, and dice potatoes. Boil until tender. Drain and mash with no seasoning. Mix well, potatoes and all other ingredients, except oil. Store, covered in refrigerator for 1 to 1 1/2 hours to set. Make patties to desired size. In skillet, (with 1 inch deep hot oil)
fry on both sides until lightly browned (turning only once).

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass baking dish).
Microwave chocolate and margarine in a large microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended. Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and walnuts until well blended.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudge crumbs.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan; cut into squares. Makes 24 fudge brownies.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange apples, pears or peaches in greased square pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle over sliced fruit of your choice.
Bake until topping is golden brown and fruit is tender, about 30 minutes.

title: hippopotamus stew
directions: Cut hippopotamus into bite-sized pieces.
This should take only about 2 weeks if you have a sharp knife.
Simmer hippopotamus for one week with salt, pepper, garlic salt and brown gravy.
This recipe will serve 3,800.
If extra servings are needed, add the rabbit; but only if needed, because most people don't like hare in their stew.

title: german fruit cake
directions: Cream together 2 cups sugar with 3/4 cup oleo; add whole eggs, one at a time and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

Mix 3 cups flour, allspice, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda with the buttermilk. Mix sugar and flour mixture, alternating with buttermilk, then fold in 2/3 cup apricot preserves, 2/3 cup pineapple preserves, 2/3 cup cherry preserves and 1 cup nuts.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in tube pan at 325°.
Better if it sets 2 to 3 days.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, eggs and buttermilk; set aside. Combine 4 cups All-Bran and boiling water; let stand 5 minutes. Add to shortening mixture.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Mix flour, milk and baking powder until well blended.
Heat oil to medium-high temperature in a large frypan.
Dip onion rings in batter, coating well.
Let excess batter drip off. Fry 2 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towel.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Combine salt, sugar and shortening.
Cream well.
Add cold water and yeast that has been dissolved in the 1/2 cup warm water. Add well beaten egg and 2 cups flour.
Stir until smooth, then add 2 2/3 cups flour, dough will be a little soft.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and put in refrigerator at least 2 hours before using.
Overnight is better.

title: easy taco casserole
directions: In a saucepan, brown ground beef.
Add salsa, Miracle Whip and chili powder.
Mix well.
In an ungreased 2 qt. baking dish, layer half of meat mixture, chips and cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 -25 minutes.
Just before serving top with tomatoes and lettuce.
(Serves 6.)

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour all fruit into bowl.
Sprinkle lemon juice over fruit and stir in dry pudding mix.
Stir and chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together, then roll into balls about the size of a quarter. Place in microwave-safe dish. Microwave for 3 minutes.

title: chicken in white wine sauce
directions: Place chicken cutlets in casserole, leaving some space between.
Cutlets may be placed on top of one another, if necessary.
Add 2 cans of condensed soup and the wine.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Cover casserole with lid or foil and bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: fried rice
directions: In a medium skillet, cook the chicken, onion and mushrooms in the oil until tender, add rice and soy sauce. Cook over a low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occassionally with a fork. Add egg, parsley and pepper. Cook for a further 5 minutes stirring constantly. Serves 5-6.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix until smooth and creamy.

title: pete's chicken thing
directions: Salt, pepper and flour chicken.
Brown chicken and onions in small amount of shortening in large skillet.
When chicken is brown, add enough water to make gravy.
When gravy is at your consistency, add 1/2 bell pepper (chopped or in strips) for flavor.
Let simmer 15 to 20 minutes, then add Worcestershire to taste.
Let simmer an additional 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain beans.
Cut bacon into 1/2-inch pieces and cook until crisp.
Remove from grease.
Cook onion in bacon grease until tender.
Mix bacon and onion with vinegar, mustard, brown sugar, catsup and salt.
Layer drained kidney beans, lima beans and pork and beans.
Pour mix over top and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini-nut bread
directions: Mix beaten eggs and oil to vanilla and sugar; mix thoroughly. Combine remaining ingredients (nuts can be optional).
Bake in floured and greased loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: candied yams supreme
directions: Peel and parboil yams, making sure they are quite undercooked and cut into thick slices.
Place in baking casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients to make thick sauce and pour over yams. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour, basting frequently.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: emily's bean soup
directions: Boil beans in 5 c. water.
Boil 2 min., then let stand covered 1 hour.
Place ham bone in pot and 3 quarts water, simmer 1 hr.
Drain beans and add to the ham stock.
(Can use the bean water too.)
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 - 3 hrs. or until beans are tender.
Discard bones; add additional water if desired.
Yield: 5 1/2 quarts.

title: spaghetti chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken; chop in pieces.
Saute vegetables in margarine until soft, 5 minutes or so.
Cook spaghetti until barely done.
Mix soup and tomato sauce with spaghetti.
Add rest of ingredients to spaghetti and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Add grated cheese to top the last 10 minutes.)

title: pecan turtles
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Stir in sugar, condensed milk, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Reduce heat to very low.
Cook, stirring almost constantly, for 25 to 30 minutes or until candy thermometer registers 245° or a small amount of mixture dropped in very cold water forms a firm ball.
Take care to prevent sticking.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Combine cranberries, water, cinnamon, cloves and orange zest. Boil until berries pop.
Strain liquid into large pitcher or container.
Add orange juice, water, lemonade and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: cheese cake for microwave
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch glass pie plate in microwave oven for about 45 seconds on High.
Add cracker crumbs to melted butter and mix well with a fork.
Press mixture evenly over bottom and sides. Cook, uncovered, in microwave oven for 2 minutes on High. Rotate plate halfway through cooking period (if you don't have a turntable).
Soften cream cheese in a small glass bowl in microwave oven for 1 minute on High.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and eggs to cream cheese.
Mix until blended.
Pour filling into crust.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Add sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine together and cook over medium heat.
Stir in vanilla, salt and peanut butter and oatmeal. Pour into well buttered shallow baking dish.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put nutmeg on bottom of pan, then peaches.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, egg and milk and mix well.
Spread over fruit and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain fruit well in advance.
Use juice for other purposes. Combine fruit, coconut and marshmallows in large bowl.
Stir in sour cream; blend thoroughly.
Pres into "presentation" bowl or pan and refrigerate.

title: grandma's apple stack ginger cake
directions: Prepare Grandma's Old Fashioned Gingerbread.
Pat into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Split each cake in half, making 4 thin cakes.
Cook applesauce in crock-pot until thick. Add cinnamon and sugar to taste.
Frost cake layers with applesauce mixture.

title: microwave reuben casserole
directions: Place sauerkraut in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Top with beef, then the cheese.
Combine salad dressings and stir; spread over cheese.
Top with tomato slices.
Set aside.

title: spinach balls
directions: Defrost spinach (squeeze out all water).
Beat the 5 eggs. Mix all the ingredients in a large bowl; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, take one tablespoon of mix, roll into ball and place on cookie tray.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad with sour cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight.
A banana may be added just before serving.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in large mixing bowl. Stir in cereal.
Add buttermilk, oil and eggs and blend until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not stir batter again.
Mixture may be stored in non-metal bowl in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks. Fill lightly greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
If desired, lightly brush melted butter over batter and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar before baking.
Makes 4 dozen. Recipe may be halved.

title: macey's macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil desired amount of noodles.
When noodles are fully cooked, place a layer in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Add second layer.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Continue layers until all noodles are used.
Melt cheese in oven at a temperature of 350°.
Serve hot!

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa.
Bring to rolling boil, turn fire down and cook 5 minutes.
Take off of fire and stir in peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: creamed hash browns
directions: Mix all
ingredients except corn flakes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle corn flakes over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Add yeast to the warm water.
Allow to sit for 10 minutes or more.
Add salt.
Pour the flour on a table or board and make a well in the center of the flour.
Pour water and yeast mixture into the well slowly, mixing in the flour as you pour.
Work the dough, adding flour if needed.
Knead dough until you have a smooth elastic ball.
Place dough in a bowl.
Cover with a towel and put in a warm place.
Allow the dough to rise until double in bulk. Place on pizza pan.
Put whatever you like on it.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix, refrigerate and serve.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in casserole dish.
Add 1 cup of grated cheese and 2 cups potato chips (crumbled).
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: squash pie
directions: Drain cooked squash and mash.
Mix together sugar, egg yolks and flour, adding a little milk to make a smooth paste.
Add remaining milk, squash, butter and lemon juice; cook until thick, stirring as needed.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites to make meringue, at room temperature, adding 4 tablespoons sugar as you beat.
Put on pie and bake at 425° until meringue is brown, about 5 to 8 minutes, depending on oven, checking often.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix according to package.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch or Bundt pan.
Beat cheese, margarine and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk, egg and vanilla.
Pour evenly over cake batter.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely. Store in refrigerator.
You may use a chocolate glaze if desired.

title: mrs. fisk's green tomato relish
directions: In a large kettle, mix the tomatoes, onions and salt and let stand overnight.
Drain mixture; put back into kettle and add the remaining ingredients; cook over medium heat until boiling.
Boil for 5 to 10 minutes and put into hot, sterilized pint jars and cover to seal.

title: formula
directions: Boil water and cool.
Pour into a large plastic container. Empty contents of can of formula.
Shake well.
Pour into a bottle and serve.
Enjoy.

title: anderson's chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add 1/2 cup sugar, salt, cocoa, butter and milk.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add remaining sugar that has been mixed with flour and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue made from egg whites.
Brown in medium oven.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and butter; add vanilla.
Beat eggs and add milk. Combine with other ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into well-buttered casserole and bake at 350° until firm, about 45 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam to prevent sticking.
Peel and slice potatoes in bottom of dish.
If you use soup, drain green beans and pour them on top of potatoes.
If you do not use soup, do not drain green beans.
Add margarine and top with pork chops. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in oven at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown on top.
Turn pork chops over and bake for another 10 to 15 minutes until pork chops are done.

title: six cup salad
directions: Drain oranges.
Combine ingredients.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with red maraschino cherries.

title: cheese dip
directions: Heat and blend all ingredients.
Serve in fondue pot or serving dish
that
will keep mixture fairly warm.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Boil until spins a thread.
Add peanuts.
Cook until slightly turned color.
Remove from stove. Add butter and soda; stir thoroughly.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, cornstarch and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until boiling.
Cook until clear. Remove from heat.
Add red food coloring (approximately 1/2 teaspoon) and Jell-O.
Stir well.
Let cool.
Mix sliced strawberries in Jell-O mixture and pour into pie shell.
Chill. Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes or until done.
Add Mozzarella to 1/2 pound cooked pasta.
Add sauce. Serves 2.

title: broccoli delight salad
directions: Use a large salad bowl and combine the broccoli, raisins and onion. In a separate bowl combine the sugar, vinegar, and mayonnaise. Mix well. Pour over broccoli mixture and toss to coat. Refrigerate to chill. Cook bacon slices and crumble. Just before serving, sprinkle with bacon and sunflower seeds. Makes 6-8 servings.

title: marilyn's burger loaf
directions: Saute onions in the butter and then add the bread.
Set aside. Mix in a bowl burger, eggs, oregano or basil, salt and garlic salt.
Then add the onions, bread and the cheese.
Mix and put in a greased loaf pan.

title: corn meal dumplings
directions: Combine corn meal, salt and pepper.
Gradually add to boiling water, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir until smooth.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients except flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto floured wax paper.
Roll around on the flour to form balls.
Drop into boiling meat or chicken stew.
Cover tightly and steam 10 minutes.

title: cheesy beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in melted butter.
As meat begins to turn color, add onion. Saute until meat is well browned.
Stir in tomato sauce and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Combine sour cream, cottage cheese, carrots and cooked noodles.
Mix well. Alternate layers of meat mixture and cottage cheese mixture in a greased 3-quart casserole dish, beginning and ending with noodles. Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hot spiced cider(serves 50.)
directions: Tie spices lightly in cheesecloth bag. Add spices and sugar to cider. Heat slowly to boiling. Lower heat to simmer 15 minutes. Remove spice bag. Serve piping hot.

title: polish potato pancakes
directions: Combine potatoes, flour, egg, salt, black pepper and grated onion.
Heat shortening in skillet.
Drop potato mixture by serving spoonfuls into hot shortening.
Brown on both sides. Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve hot with applesauce or grape jelly.

title: squash stew
directions: Cube or slice squash.
Dice tomatoes, pepper and onion.
Add seasoning to taste.
Add to squash and simmer one hour or until done.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Mix and chill good.
It will keep for 3 or 4 days in closed container.

title: licking good chuck
directions: Thoroughly coat both sides of meat with the sauces, mustard and catsup.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Place in roasting pan and bake at 350° until done, as desired.

title: frozen sweet pickles
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and set in refrigerator 2 hours. Drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Pour over cucumbers. Bag and freeze.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Combine chicken broth, water, mushrooms, cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar and pepper sauce in medium saucepan. Bring to a boil over high
heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Gradually pour egg into boiling soup, stirring constantly in one direction.
Remove from heat; stir in green onions.
Garnish with additional chopped green onions or cilantro as desired.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a greased 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bunco party spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze dry the spinach.
Set aside.
In a medium bowl, blend vegetable recipe soup mix, sour cream, mayonnaise, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, lemon juice, Tabasco sauce and Lea & Perrins sauce.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts.
Put mixture in serving bowl and top with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Chill for at least 3 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips, salsa and extra sour cream. Also good with crumbled Blue cheese sprinkled in mixture.

title: ground beef hash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using Dutch oven, brown beef, onions and green pepper.
Drain fat. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: hoppin' john(black-eyed peas and rice)
directions: Cook peas according to directions on package.
Bring water and salt to a boil; add rice.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender (approximately 20 to 25 minutes).
Combine bacon fat, rice, peas and onions in frypan; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Heat until all are warm.
Stir in bacon and serve.

title: drunken hot dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
If it dries out, add more bourbon.
Transfer to chafing dish and serve with toothpicks.

title: witches brew
directions: Bring water to boil; add tea bags and steep 20 to 30 minutes. Remove the tea bags. Add remaining ingredients and simmer. May be refrigerated and reheated for 2 to 3 days. A great cold weather drink.

title: herbed rolled flounder
directions: Lay fillets, smooth side down.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon parsley, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Roll up each from wide end; secure with wooden pick.
Bring broth to boiling in skillet.
Add flounder.
Simmer, covered, 8 to 10 minutes until fish flakes easily.
Remove with slotted spoon to platter.
Remove skillet from heat.
Whisk in yogurt and mustard.
Add remaining parsley.
Spoon over fish.

title: new england baked beans
directions: Simmer beans in 9 cups unsalted water for 30 minutes.
Allow to stand, covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until beans are softened. Drain and put in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients except bacon; mix well.
Place bacon strips on top.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or on high 4 to 6 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: curious cake
directions: Combine
cake
mix,
margarine and 1/3 cup of the milk; mix well.
Press
of
the	mixture
into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake
at 350° for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over baked crust.
Melt caramels with remaining 1/3
cup milk in saucepan over low heat; stir often until mixture
is smooth.
Spread
evenly over nuts and chips.
Top with
remaining cake
mixture;
press
gently.
Bake
for
20 minutes at 350°. Cool slightly.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water in a bowl.
Add pie filling and pineapple and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; chill until firm.
Blend cream cheese and sugar in a bowl.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Spread over congealed layer.
Top with nuts and coconut, if desired.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish with vanilla wafers. Pour on 1/2 of following mixture.
Heat strawberries and sugar, then stir in jello.
Cool.
Pour over vanilla wafers.

title: fitatchia
directions: Roll dough flat.
Place meats, mushrooms and sauce on dough. Roll dough like a nut roll.
Form a circle.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecue potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Chop onion, celery and boiled eggs.
Mix all these together with pickle relish.
Drain potatoes and cool slightly.
Add to mixture and mix.
Add mustard, vinegar, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Mix thoroughly.
You may need to add more mayonnaise to obtain proper consistency.
You may adjust any of the ingredients to suit your taste.

title: walking tostada
directions: Layer all ingredients on a large platter (12-inch pizza pan works well) in order given (adding shredded lettuce after tomatoes, if used).
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: pork chop wild rice casserole
directions: Wash and drain rice.
Place in a quart casserole.
Add the broth, wine and onion.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover; top each chop with slice of apple, then a slice of tomato.
Re-cover; continue baking for 30 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
Serves 4.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Stir tomatoes, onion, chilies and seasonings into avocados by hand.
Chill and serve on lettuce.

title: sicilian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
In a large skillet, simmer oil, garlic, onions and parsley until tender. Combine tomato paste and water.
Add the tomato puree, wine and seasonings.
Continue to simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Add bell peppers. Simmer an additional 2 minutes until tender.
Pour over pasta and blend.
Garnish with black olives.
Chill approximately 1 to 2 hours.
Serve cold.

title: no bake cake
directions: Crumble cake and spread evenly in bottom of a large oblong pan.
Pour pineapple evenly over cake.
Heat milk and marshmallows in saucepan over low heat until marshmallows are dissolved.
Pour this evenly over layer of pineapple.
Prepare Dream Whip and spread over cake to create frosting effect.
Sprinkle coconut over top.
Chill.

title: kansas city dressing
directions: Beat well and strain.
Pour into 2 pint jars.
Add garlic cloves in each jar. Watch that garlic doesn't fall into salad.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: In a bowl, mix together flour and sugar. Set aside.
Mix margarine, oil, cocoa and water together in a saucepan.
Heat until comes to a boil.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture and beat.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Beat again.
Pour into a greased and floured 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or so. Frost with chocolate frosting and sprinkle with nutmeats, if desired.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix together water, sugar, salt and shortening; let cool. Soften 2 cakes yeast in 1/4 cup warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar. Add 2 well beaten eggs to first mixture, then add yeast to that. Add enough flour gradually until you get a dough you can roll out. Cover bowl and place in refrigerator.
Will keep 6 to 7 days.
When ready to use, make into buns; let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: orange nog
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in blender until smooth.
With blender running at lowest speed, add ice cubes, one at a time; blend smooth.
Serve at once.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: super carrot cake
directions: Combine carrots and lemon juice.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, spices and salt in a bowl.
Beat in eggs, one at a time and stir in vanilla, coconut, walnuts, dates and pineapple until well blended.
Pour into greased pans (2 loaf pans).
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean and cakes shrink away from sides of pan (approximately 60 minutes).

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except brown sugar together.
Pour in prepared pan and add brown sugar to the top of batter.
Bake at 325° for about 55 minutes.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix all vegetables in large dish.
Add linguine and salad dressing.
Chill.
Add croutons when served.
Season to taste.
Add a small amount of cooking oil to boiling water and linguine will not stick together.

title: casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Put bread crumbs on top.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine and beat well.
Add 10-ounce bottle of 7-Up.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Prepare orange juice as directed.
Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes.
When cool, add pineapple and orange juice.
Mix bananas with the juice of lemons in blender and add to pineapple mixture. Freeze.
When ready to serve, pour ginger ale or 7-Up over frozen mixture.
Serve slushy.

title: "syrup for pancakes"
directions: Mix; boil for 3 minutes and serve.

title: no icing chocolate cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine; add flavoring and nuts.
Combine sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla and add to chocolate mixture. Spoon into muffin pans lined with paper cups.
Fill half full. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple nut fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; cool.
Chill until thickened. Combine salad dressing mixed with the milk.
Fold into jello and add pineapple, cottage cheese, nuts and lemon juice.
Chill until firm.
I use a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil small or medium potatoes until done.

Remove from pan. Put same amount of butter or margarine as the size of potatoes. Mash together until all lumps are gone, then add confectioners sugar to butter and potatoes until it has the texture of dough bread.
Roll with rolling pin until thin.
Spread with peanut butter to 1/2-inch from the edge.
Roll into a long roll and cut off the ends.
Chill.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine milk, lemonade and Cool Whip in a large bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until blended.
Pour into pie shells and refrigerate for at least 4 hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: yellow frosted punch
directions: Add required amount of water to juice.
Freeze pineapple juice and take from freezer 2 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale last.
Serves 40 or more.

title: aunt hazel's sweet pickles
directions: Drain and rinse pickles.
Slice into large crock and cover with ice.
Let stand until all ice melts; drain.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over pickles.
Stir every morning for 5 days. Pack and seal.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli following directions on back of package.
Drain and place in greased baking casserole.
Make cheese sauce as follows:
melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Stir together. Pour milk gradually, a little at a time.
Add cheese and stir over medium heat until thick.
Crumble 1/2 package Ritz crackers on top.
Pour 1/2 of sauce over crackers. Crumble remainder of crackers over sauce.
Pour on remainder of sauce. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cherry torte
directions: *This is correct: 1 teaspoon, not tablespoon.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sausage, hash browns and cheese on crust.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over top of sausage mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Make up to 8 hours ahead.
Store in refrigerator until ready to bake.

title: nutty graham cake
directions: Beat eggs well and add other ingredients.
Bake at 325°.

title: daiquiri punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine orange juice concentrate, pink lemonade and daiquiri mix.
Stir in water, nectar and Schnapps. Chill until needed.
At serving time, add lemon-lime soda and some ice cubes.
Garnish with strawberries, if desired.

title: seafood rice bowl
directions: Combine rice with rest of ingredients.
Chestnuts should be drained and sliced.
Mix well and pour into a buttered 2 1/2 quart casserole.
Toast almonds.
Sprinkle mixture with nuts, cheese and some paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: nine bean soup mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Divide into 10 (2 cup) packages or jars for gift giving.
The beans look pretty layered in glass containers.
Pack with soup bowls or in a soup tureen.
Include recipe for soup.

title: praline cookies
directions: Boil together for 2 minutes the brown sugar and butter.
Line bottom of jelly roll pan with graham crackers.
Pour mixture over crackers and bake 12 minutes at 325°.
When cool, break crackers on line.
Good!

title: chicken soup
directions: Skim grease from broth and pull chicken from bone.
Cut green onions with tops and add to broth.
Cook slow.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Add cooked carrots and broccoli.
Add chicken and rest of seasonings.
Remove from heat.
Add half and half and heat later to eat.
Will thicken some second time heating.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil broccoli until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
Melt butter/margarine.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Add milk; cook to a medium consistency (not too thin or too thick).
Add bouillon cube and soup.
Heat to medium boil.
Add cooked broccoli.
Simmer 10 minutes.
(I use the pot I cook the broccoli in to make the thickening.
I use canned milk.)
tags: cream of broccoli soup with cheese

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Peel and cut the rhubarb into small pieces.
Boil slowly until tender.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved.
Serve hot or cold. Makes 6 servings.
May add 2 cups sliced strawberries.

title: spanish yellow rice with green pigeon peas
directions: Spanish products can be found in Spanish section.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place all in the blender and blend till smooth.
Makes 1 1/4 cups, the equivalent of 1 can of sweetened condensed milk.

title: grilled chicken teriyaki
directions: Place chicken in pan and pour all ingredients over breasts. Let marinate for 1 hour.
Place on foil on grill and cover with foil.
Cook for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: greek salad
directions: Place romaine, tomatoes, olives, cheese and oregano in a large bowl.
Toss with dressing.
Makes 10 servings.

title: nutty cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo and 3/4 cup pecans.
Press in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix brown sugar and cream cheese and spread over 1st layer.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Cool before cutting.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease six 3 x 6-inch pans or two 9 x 5-inch pans. Sift dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center. Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten. Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes for small pans. Additional time will be needed for larger pans. Check at intervals.
Remove from oven and let cool 5 minutes before removing from pans. Cool on wire rack.

title: southern style potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese; stir well.
Spoon into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Crush cornflakes and stir in remaining butter.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: crispy onion rolls
directions: Combine butter and onion mix.
Pour 1/2 of the onion mix in a greased round 8-inch pan.
Arrange biscuits and pour rest of butter mixture over them.
Bake at 400° for 12 or 14 minutes. Serve with lots of hot melted garlic butter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: frances' butterscotch pie
directions: Mix in a pan the brown sugar, margarine and 4 tablespoons "cream".
Cook this mixture until thick and brown.

title: goop
directions: Combine food coloring and water.
Add cornstarch, a little at a time.
Stir mixture until texture is even.
For added fun, mix up a big batch to use in sand and water table for exploration with cups, funnels, etc.

title: godfrey brownies
directions: If you use plain flour, add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon baking powder.

title: hungarian short ribs
directions: In Dutch
oven	brown
meat
in
hot
oil.
Add onions; blend together
tomato
sauce, 1 cup water, brown sugar, vinegar,
salt, mustard
and
Worcestershire
sauce and pour over meat.
Cover and simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Skim off fat.	Stir in noodles and other cup of water.
Cover and cook on low heat for 20 minutes. Stir often.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot dog appetizers
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in crock-pot.
Slice hot dogs and simmer in mixture in crock-pot until ready to serve.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put into a large baking pan. Then spread ketchup over top.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes, keeping grease drained off.

title: western slaw
directions: Shake together salt, mustard, oil, vinegar, sugar and pepper and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps about 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine rhubarb, marshmallows, Jell-O and sugar in a large mixing bowl; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and cool.
Prepare vegetables and mix together in a large airtight container.
Any of the following may be substituted or added:
mushrooms, celery, radishes, cherry tomatoes or zucchini.

title: tuna jellied salad(low calorie)
directions: Dissolve gelatine in juice from mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell; set aside.
Preheat oven to 325°.
In a medium saucepan, low heat, melt butter.
Add cocoa and stir until smooth.
Remove from heat; cool.
Stir in sugar, salt, slightly beaten eggs and corn syrup.
Blend well.
Stir in chopped nuts if desired and pour all into pie crust.
Place pecan halves on top. Bake 40 minutes.
Let cool and cover for 8 hours before serving.

title: crabmeat teche
directions: *Equivalent amount of canned Alaskan King crabmeat may be substituted.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix each ingredient well, one at a time, and refrigerate at least an hour before serving.

title: old-fashioned soft pumpkin cookies
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla.
Beat until light and creamy.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Smooth tops of cookies. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Dip eggplant into egg, then into seasoned bread crumbs.
Fry eggplant on both sides.
Place on paper towels to dry off excess oil.
Coat bottom of a large casserole dish with sauce.
Place eggplant on top.
Add filling.
Place eggplant on top. Coat with sauce. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add baking powder.
Add flour, a little at a time until all is used up.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mark's chicken chili
directions: Combine all ingredients with water.
Simmer until beans are tender.
Omit red pepper if desired (for milder chili).
Remove bay leaf when done.

title: jane's dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate at least 2 hours (overnight is better).
May be kept in tightly closed container for 1 week.
Good with crackers or veggies.

title: texas jam cake
directions: Blend sugar, butter, jam and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture, blending well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake in three greased and floured layer pans at 350° for 35 minutes or until tests done in center with toothpick.
Cool.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer cabbage, onions, potatoes and carrots in several layers, sprinkling each with seasoned salt.
Lay strips of bacon on top.
Pour water in at corner of pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: parisian balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Using approximately 1 teaspoon batter, roll into a ball and place on a cookie sheet.
When finished, freeze all the candy balls.
When solid, dip into a mixture of two 12 ounce packages semi-sweet chocolate chips and 3 1/2 teaspoons grated paraffin melted together over water in a double boiler.
Dip candies 2 or 3 at a time, then cool on waxed paper until hardened.
Serves 24.

title: chivicie
directions: Cut fish into thin fillets and then cube pieces about 1/4-inch square.
Add lime juice, fresh squeezed, not frozen or diluted. Let sit in refrigerator for 2 hours minimum.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Mix chunks with marshmallows and put in refrigerator overnight.
In a small pan, mix pineapple juice, sugar, flour, egg and vinegar.
Cook until thick over medium heat.
Cool overnight in refrigerator.

title: coconut crunch pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add sugar; beat for 1 minute. Add other ingredients.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with sliced bananas and Cool Whip.

title: company best pickles
directions: Cover whole cucumbers with boiling water.
Allow to stand until next morning.
Drain, repeat this procedure for the next 3 mornings.
On the fifth day, drain and slice into 1/2-inch slices. Combine sugar, spices, salt and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and pour over the cucumbers.
Let stand 2 days.
On the third day, pack the cucumbers into sterile jars, heat the syrup to boiling and pour over the cucumbers.
Seal.

title: sour cream walnuts
directions: Mix sugars and sour cream in a small saucepan.

Place over medium heat. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 240° on candy thermometer. Quickly add vanilla and nuts. Stir. When well coated, turn out on waxed paper. Separate and let set.
Best if made in sunny or dry weather.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: beef stew
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix in a heavy 5 to 6-quart Dutch oven everything except meat and fresh vegetables.
Stir in meat and vegetables.
Cover and bake at 325° for about 3 hours, stirring twice, until meat is tender and sauce is thickened.
Discard bay leaves before serving or refrigerating.
Very good served with mashed potatoes.

title: quick shish kebob
directions: Cut meat and vegetables bite size.
Place vegetables in rectangular shallow baking pan.
Pour a little over half of the salad dressing and marinate.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes until done.
Mix while baking a couple of times.
Last 10 to 15 minutes of vegetable time, add meat.
Keep about 1/4-inch of dressing in pan.
Bake meat separately in another pan.
Turn every 5
minutes.

title: cherry peach dumplings
directions: Mix water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves with cherry pie filling in a 10-inch skillet. Add peaches. Bring to a boil. Add milk to egg to make 1/2 cup. Stir into biscuit mix to form soft dough. Drop dough by tablespoon on top of boiling fruit. Cook over low heat for 10 minutes. Serve warm. Spoon fruit over dumplings and top with whipped cream topping.

title: cheese roll
directions: Grate cheese and cream cheese together.
Add other ingredients and stir until well blended.
Roll in chili powder and paprika.

title: fig newtons
directions: Combine figs, water, juice and sugar in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes or until thick; set aside.

title: toffee squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, brown sugar, and vanilla; beat in egg.
Stir in flour a little at a time.
Spread batter in a greased 13x9-inch pan.
Bake for about 15 minutes or until a light golden brown.
Break hershey bars into pieces and place on top of hot crust.
Place back into oven for a couple minutes to melt. Remove from oven and spread evenly.
Sprinkle crushed walnuts over chocolate.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: cheesed squash
directions: Pare and cut squash in small pieces; cook until tender. Drain.
Add milk slowly to mayonnaise.
When it begins to thicken, add cheese and seasonings.
Place squash in casserole.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 400° until brown on top.

title: onion batter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, salt, sugar, onion and half the flour.
Beat 2 minutes medium speed on mixer. Scrape sides and bottom of bowl frequently.
Add remaining flour; blend in with spoon until smooth.
Scrape batter from sides of bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk (about 30 minutes).
Stir down batter.
Spoon batter evenly into grease muffin pan, filling half full.
Let rise in warm place until batter reaches 1/2 inch from top of pans (about 40 minutes).
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, depending on size of pans, or until brown.
To test, tap top crust; it should sound hollow.
Immediately remove from pans to rack.
Brush tops with melted butter or shortening.
Do not place in direct draft.
Makes 9 to 12 rolls.

title: jamician sea treasure
directions: Spray Pam in a skillet and heat up.
Sear fillets on both sides.
Remove from skillet and place in a baking dish.
Toss vegetables with PickaPepper sauce.
Pour vegetable mixture over fish.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with rice.
Brown rice is especially nice with this dish.

title: betty dana's pickle relish
directions: Grind onions first and put into a side dish.
Remove pepper seeds and grind.
Pour boiling water over peppers and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: pork marinade
directions: Marinate pork chops for 2 to 4 hours.

title: refrigerated pickles
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; allow to stand 1 hour, then drain.
Add all ingredients together.
Put in 4 pint jars and refrigerate.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Chop onion, celery and parsley finely.
Saute in oleo.
When thoroughly cooked, add 1 cup crabmeat, bread crumbs, 2 slightly beaten eggs, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Add milk to moisten.
Bake in greased casserole in moderate oven 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter; return to oven only long enough to melt butter.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corncake casserole
directions: Combine corn, eggs and corn muffin mix. Mix well. Add 1 cup cheese. Spread corn mixture in greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until firm.

title: green bean salad
directions: Cook and cool green beans.
Add crumbled bacon and chopped onion.
Pour Paul Newman dressing over, mix and chill.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat
eggs.
Add melted butter, sugar and vinegar, then add raisins,
nuts
and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: low-fat salad corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until lightly browned.
Add 3 cups milk, potatoes, onions, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer about seven minutes until potatoes are tender.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix margarine, confectioners sugar, peanut butter, graham crackers and vanilla together.
Roll into balls and chill.

title: zucchini (apple) pie
directions: Mix all together as you would for apple pie filling. Place in pie shell and top with crust. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes until tender.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into two balls.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: chicken in a pot
directions: Place celery, carrots and onion in bottom of crock-pot.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle with tarragon, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth.
Cook on medium-high 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cheese chili appetizers
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Add flour, baking powder, chopped chilies, cottage cheese and shredded Jack cheese and mix until blended. Turn batter into pan and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes longer.
Cut into squares and serve hot.
Can be made early and refrigerated.
Enjoy!

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix and spoon into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: raisin pie
directions: Melt and brown butter in saucepan.
Add flour and blend.
Add honey and cook, stirring for 2 or 3 minutes until slightly thickened.
Add raisins, salt, spices and water; bring to a boil. Put pie crust in pie pan; slice apples in bottom.
Pour raisin mixture on top.
Add top crust and brown in oven.

title: pinto beans with hamburger meat
directions: Cook hamburger meat, strain
grease off.
Put meat in a deep skillet or pan and	put
tomato
sauce
and 4 cans water. Add onion, chili powder,
barbecue
sauce,
salt
and
pepper. Cook for one hour.
Add	water as needed.
Cook pinto beans in another pot until done.
Pour
off water.
Pour sauce into the beans and cook for 15 minutes,
slow.
You
may
need to add a little water if it is too thick.

title: roquefort cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in covered jar and refrigerate. Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: coffee bars
directions: Mix coffee and oil together first, then add the rest of ingredients.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle chocolate bits and walnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli - rice casserole
directions: Mix cooked rice and drained broccoli.
Combine Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup.
Mix rice and broccoli with cheese mixture and celery.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, water and cocoa to boil.
Add sugar, flour, eggs, milk, soda and vanilla.
Pour into lightly greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Mix chopped candy, dates and nuts with 1/2 cup flour.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix soda in buttermilk and mix all together.
Turn into greased, floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 300°.

title: english toffee
directions: Boil sugar and butter to 310° or hard crack stage in water. Cool slightly then add vanilla.
Pour on aluminum foil immediately and put chocolate bars on top to melt.
Sprinkle with nuts, smooth over top.
When cold, crack into piece.

title: m&m's cookies for kids
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Beat in vanilla, water and eggs. Sift dry ingredients together and add to the first mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten.
Press 3 to 5 M&M's into each cookie.
Kids love to help with this part and may slip a few into their pockets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Bag spices in cheesecloth (remove bag before canning).
The night before, cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix brine, using enough salt to float an egg.
Use enamel or earthen container. Soak tomato slices for about 6 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Cook vinegar, sugar and bag of spices for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Cook until transparent.
Don't overcook!
Remove bag. Fill jars and seal.
This recipe is 90 years old!

title: cheese pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Add cheese.
Cut in Crisco.
Add water. See recipe for Chicken Cheese Turnovers.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in pineapple juice over low heat, folding until smooth.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Blend cheese, carrots and pineapple.
When jello is cooled, add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 1-quart ring mold.
Chill.

title: buttermilk orange shakes
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth.
Or beat all ingredients with hand beater.

title: betty's apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, then turn oven back to 300° and bake 20 minutes more.
Use tube pan.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and peppers in a large bowl; add salt and garlic.
Mix well.
Add ice cubes; let stand for 2 hours. Drain well.
Combine vinegar, sugar, turmeric, mustard and celery seed in a large kettle; boil well.
Add chopped vegetables.
Heat just until boiling.
Put in sterilized pint jars within one inch of top.
Process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes, or pressure canner at 10 pounds pressure for 4 minutes.
Makes 9 pints.
Great for using in salads.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, mix together sugar, salt and milk.
Boil to the soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat fudge until dull looking. It should appear to be getting thick.
Quickly spread into lightly buttered pan.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg.
Add flour; mix well.
Press dough on bottom and 2 inches high around sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk.
Spread spinach in 1-quart casserole.
Top with cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Drain; let stand 5 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Sift 1/2 dry ingredients into sugar mixture; blend.
Sift in remaining dry ingredients alternately with eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots and mix well, then mix in nuts.
Bake in a 325° oven approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes in lightly oiled 10-inch tube pan.
Cool in pan upright.

title: merv's hot chili(makes 24 servings)
directions: Brown cut-up and ground flank steak in 2 tablespoons of the oil in kettle or Dutch oven; lower heat, cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for about 45 minutes.

title: peach and blueberry crisp
directions: Spread peaches over 9 or 10-inch glass baking dish.
Spread blueberries over peaches.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; sprinkle over blueberries.
Sprinkle lemon juice and nuts evenly over the mixture.
In a small bowl, mix flour, remaining sugar and salt.
Put in butter.
Spread over fruit.
Bake at 370° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: low-fat, sugar-free strawberry shake
directions: Place ingredients in blender. Blend until smooth and well mixed. Use more or less milk, depending on how thick you like it. Enjoy!

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all items in a large bowl and chill.
Quick and easy for a salad or dessert.

title: tender biscotti
directions: Mix oleo and sugar, adding 1 egg at a time with electric mixer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mixture will be soft.
Oil hands and shape into loaves about 2-inches wide and 1-inch high. Place in greased cookie sheet (3 rolls).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and slice about 1/2-inch thick.
Lay on sides back on cookie sheet.
Bake about 6 minutes on each side at 350°.
(One cup walnuts is optional.)

title: haupia pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, mix together coconut milk, sugar and water.
Cook over medium heat.
Add cornstarch mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: "ranch lentils"
directions: Rinse lentils.
In heavy saucepan, bring lentils, salt and 4 cups water to boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until water is absorbed and lentils are tender.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix ingredients as given.
Thickness of batter depends on carrots.
Shred very fine or grate (15 1/2 ounce can of pineapple is enough for a double recipe).
Makes two loaves.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: strawberry bread
directions: In a large bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Set aside.
In a medium bowl, mix together eggs, strawberries, oil and nuts.
Fold into flour mixture, stirring just enough to moisten.
Spoon into two well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until they test done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Chopped candied ginger may be used in place of ground ginger.

title: crockpot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Place in all other ingredients and mix well.
Cook on low for 3 hours.
No need to stir white cooking.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, seasoning as desired with salt and pepper; drain.
Saute onion in the butter or margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a lightly greased casserole. Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Peel zucchini and cut into pieces. Chop onion and boil with zucchini until cooked. Drain. Add all other ingredients except bread crumbs. Toast bread crumbs and crumble over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: anne's homemade biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add Crisco and knead until like pancake dough.
Add milk and mix well.
Roll out dough, flour and cut biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
(If they don't brown, turn on broil for a little.)

title: glazed carrots
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 1 minute.
Add carrots.
Heat 1 more minute and serve.

title: sarah's chicken
directions: Combine small jar Russian dressing, onion soup and apricot preserves.
Pour over chicken breasts (skinned and boned).
Bake 1 hour at 325°, uncovered.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cut broccoli so that each floweret has about a 1 inch stalk. Boil water; place flowerets in colander above water and cover. When broccoli turns to a drab green and stalks are fork-tender, drain water from pot, reserving about 1/3 cup of the water.
Cook tortellini according to package directions.
While tortellini is cooking, brown garlic, parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Mix browned garlic mixture, water that was reserved and the steamed broccoli.
Blend very well.
Add hot tortellini to mixture and blend again.
Let set for 1/2 hour at room temperature and then refrigerate.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until well done (crumbled), then drain.
Prepare pie crust (from scratch or homemade).
Mix cheese and sausage. Sprinkle in shell.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
pour in shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
