Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed cabbage czechoslovakian style
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well.
Core cabbage; put in boiling water to soften.
Wrap meat and rice mixture in cabbage leaves. Cover bottom of large pan with sauerkraut.
Line cabbage rolls on top.
Can make a double row.
Cover with water.
Cook on low flame 4 hours.
Keep water high.

title: pineapple cheesecake squares
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl with fork until crumbly. Press firmly and evenly in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Bake until set at 350° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes (do not brown).

title: lemon fluff
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water.
Combine with the sugar and lemon juice and rind.
Chill until thick and syrupy. Whip with fork and fold into the evaporated milk, whipped with rotary beater as stiff as it will stand.
Pile into a pan which has been lined with graham cracker mixture.

title: thousand island salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Cover and chill.

title: chicken in pastry
directions: Roll out and separate crescent rolls.
Place chicken breast on one roll section.
Place another roll section on top.
Crimp edges. Brush tops with beaten egg.
Cook in 425° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve with cranberry sauce.

title: home baked beans
directions: Wash and pick over beans.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
Next morning, simmer beans in salted water until tender to bite.
Drain and save water.
Place in bottom of large bean pot or crock-pot.
Alternately layer cooked beans with a mixture of brown sugar, tomatoes, onions, mustard, salt and pepper.
Top with bacon.
Add enough of water in which beans were cooked to cover beans.
Cover with lid; cook until tender.
If using crock-pot, put on low for 8 to 10 hours, stirring occasionally.
Do not add extra water.

title: cornell whole wheat bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Add the sesame seed, pumpkin or sunflower seeds, raisins and dry yeast; mix lightly with first ingredients.
In a large bowl, combine the brown sugar, molasses, 2 cups warm water and the egg.
Mix or combine lightly. Add dry ingredients to liquid mixture gradually.
Beat with mixer as you add dry ingredients to liquid mixture for as long as the mixer will do the job.
When batter becomes too stiff, continue adding dry ingredients by hand, working batter for at least 5 minutes, kneading until firm and elastic.
Turn onto floured board.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In separate bowl, mix pineapple, egg and milk.
Melt butter.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Add pineapple mixture to flour mixture. After stirring well, add nuts.
Stir.
Bake in bread pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chili-cheese bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bring cheeses to room temperature. Combine crumbs and margarine in an 8-inch square pan.
Press onto the bottom and up the sides of the pan, forming a crust.
Bake for 10 minutes and set aside.
Reduce oven heat to 250°.
In a large mixing bowl, blend cheeses at medium speed.
Add cayenne and garlic.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Fold in chilies and onion.
Pour into prepared crust and bake 1 hour until set.
Cool and cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve at room temperature or slightly chilled.
Makes 64 bite sized appetizers.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour mixture into greased pan.
Bake approximately 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Cut into squares.
Serve.

title: aldine baked beans
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix melted butter with crushed crackers and press into pan. Mix ice cream, pudding and milk.
Pour over crust.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with candy bars.

title: easy persimmon pudding
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Chop oranges up fine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan and spread into it.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
When just cool enough to work, take a spatula and lift up from pan. Start rolling into balls the size of walnuts.
(A little water will help your hands not to stick to the cookies while rolling.) Then roll in powdered sugar.

title: stuffed date drops
directions: Stuff dates with nut halves.
Cream shortening and sugar until light; beat in egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream to creamed mixture.
Stir in dates.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fancy toast
directions: Spread on English muffins and toast/bake until ready.

title: zarda(sweet rice with saffron)
directions: Cook rice partially in a large amount of boiling water.
Drain in colander, spread on a large plate or board and allow to cool. Pop cardamom pods between fingers but let them remain whole.
Break cinnamon into several pieces.

title: baked sausage meat, sweet potatoes and fruit
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook sweet potatoes, peel and cut them into thin slices.
Grease baking dish.
Cover the bottom with 1/2 the sweet potatoes.
Shape sausage into 4 flat cakes. Brown the cakes slightly in a greased pan.
Then add bacon.
Peel and cut apples or pineapple slices into thick slices.

title: tangy wiener bites
directions: Combine gravy and water.
Blend.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat until sauce thickens and meat is heated through. Serve with toothpicks.

title: aunt eleanor's 24-hour salad
directions: Combine all.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and clear.
Cool slightly.

title: garlic dressing
directions: Mix all together in blender.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Add Blue cheese, if desired.
Shake well before serving.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Beat milk, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Pour into pie crust.

title: ridgefield's dressing
directions: Mix in order with high speed mixer.
It should turn "white" immediately.

title: scalloped corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in deep casserole dish.
It must be a deep dish or 9 x 13-inch pan because the mixture rises as it bakes.
Add the sour cream and eggs, mix well.
Stir in both cans of corn, corn bread mix and onion and/or pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients until well blended and spoon into loaf pans.

title: hard tack(cinnamon candy)
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water and coloring to 305° (hard crack stage).
Add cinnamon oil or desired flavoring.
Pour into buttered pan.
Crack when mixture becomes hard.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add egg yolks. Add raisins. Beat egg whites stiff and fold in lightly. Put in pastry shell and bake in a slow oven for 45 minutes.

title: bacon-cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, onion and cheese in pie plate.
In blender or processor, combine remaining ingredients and beat on high about one minute, until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes. Cut into wedges.
Serve with salad.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix in order (sugar, flour, cocoa, eggs, margarine, milk, water, pecans, coconut and vanilla) and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Mix well in a large bowl and let set in refrigerator 3 or 4 hours or overnight.
You can add miniature marshmallows.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 370°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir together dry ingredients; gradually add to shortening mix.
Mix well; stir in mincemeat.
Drop by rounded teaspoon 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until light brown.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and sour milk.
Sift all dry ingredients together; beat in part of dry ingredients before adding cherries and nuts.
Makes 2 layers.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Use cherry juice for frosting instead of milk.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients mixing well.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions on package. In casserole dish, melt butter with onion. Brown hamburger and drain. Layer the casserole dish with the following: spaghetti, hamburger, spaghetti sauce, Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella and Swiss cheese. Top with pepperoni slices. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix together with a spoon the dry jello into the yogurt, then add to the whipped topping.
Spoon into the crust.
Let set about 1 hour in the refrigerator and enjoy.

title: cheese custard
directions: Beat sugar, flour, egg yolks and salt.
Heat milk (warm), cottage cheese and pineapple.
Beat egg whites and put in last.
Bake at 400°
for 30 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: zucchini-carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until frothy.
Gradually beat in oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat at high speed 4 minutes.
Stir in carrot, zucchini and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Spread cooled cake with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 3 slices cheese and remainder of sauce in jar.
Mix together and spoon into pan (will not form shape).
Pour remainder of sauce over meat.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Remove from oven.
Drain off grease.
Put cheese on meat and place in oven until cheese melts.
Remove.
Let set 10 to 20 minutes.

title: chinese noodle salad
directions: Combine cabbage, onions, almonds, sesame seeds and noodles (broken up). Set aside. For dressing, combine all ingredients and blend well. Heat to almost boiling or microwave on high 2 minutes. Pour over cabbage mixture and toss to thoroughly coat. Refrigerate at least 6 hours. Stir occasionally.

title: cherry holiday punch
directions: Remove tags from tea bags and add to water in large container or pitcher.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight. Remove tea bags, squeezing gently against side of container. Combine tea with cranberry-apple drink, pina colada mix, lemon juice and sugar.
Keep chilled.

title: coconut layer cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time.
Alternate milk and flour.
Add salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Bake in 4 (9-inch) layers at 350° until done, about 15 minutes.

title: pistachio nut swirl cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream, vegetable oil and almond extract.
Combine the sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour 1/3 of the batter into a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with half of the sugar mixture.
Repeat layers and top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350°
for about 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before inverting pan.

title: ham and swiss casserole
directions: In greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish, layer a third of the noodles, ham and cheese.
In a small bowl, combine soup, sour cream, green pepper, and onion; spread half over the top.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40-45 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: stuffed italian bread
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and drain.
I use the links sliced. You can also use the loose if you prefer.
Cook spinach until dry. Make sure there is no liquid.
Mix sausage, spinach and cheese together until cheese is melted through.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute chopped pecans in butter, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes, or until toasted.
Set aside to cool.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into freezer and freeze about 10 minutes, or until ice cream is thick.
Remove dasher.
Add pecans. Finish freezing until firm.
Let ripen at least 1 hour.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: confectioners sugar icing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until smooth.

title: super simple soup
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
In large kettle, cook sausage, cabbage, carrot and green onions just until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and heat through.
Serves 6.

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Cut rolls in
half.
Add diced ham and cheese.	Put top half of rolls
back on.	Melt margarine and add other ingredients. Spoon over the
top of rolls.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter
or
margarine;
add eggs and cream well. Add
milk
and
dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly; add cocoa mixed
with
hot water, and beat well.
Bake at 350° in layer pans
for
30 to 35 minutes or in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 35 minutes.

title: carrot zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: In small bowl, combine 1 cup stuffing and margarine; set aside. In large bowl, combine soup and sour cream. Add zucchini, carrots, onion and remaining stuffing. Toss to mix well. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with a little stuffing mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves
5 to 6.

title: drop filled cookies
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients.
Add milk, vanilla and nuts, if you wish.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Mix all.
Drop dessert spoon of dough on sheet. Make a well.
Put teaspoon of filling in well.
Place teaspoon of dough on top.
Bake at 400°.

title: alligator stew
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper in skillet. Season to taste. Add catsup, water, pork and beans and brown sugar. Cook until onions and pepper are tender.

title: calico corn
directions: Saute butter, onion and bell pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cover with grated cheese and paprika.
Bake for 15 minutes more.

title: parmesan chicken italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Take the Italian dressing and pour it in a bowl; dip the chicken strips in the dressing. Mix the bread crumbs and the Parmesan together in a bowl; dip the dressing coated chicken into this mixture. Lay the chicken side by side along a greased pan; pour remaining dressing and bread crumb mixture over it. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Drain macaroni and mandarin oranges. Add all ingredients together. Mix gently until combined evenly. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheddar cheese puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets with vegetable shortening.
Combine milk, water, butter, salt, pepper and nutmeg in large saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil.
Add flour all at once, stirring vigorously with a wooden spoon until mixture forms a thick, smooth ball that leaves the side of the pan clean.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with a wooden spoon after each addition until paste is shiny and smooth.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Drop paste by heaping teaspoonfuls, about 1 inch apart, onto prepared sheets.
Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes.
Lower oven to 350°; bake 10 to 15 minutes, or until puffed and golden.
Turn off oven.
Prick in several places with fork.
Let puffs stand in oven for 5 minutes. Serve warm

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Mix sour cream and soda.
Set aside.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Add sour cream mixture.
Pour half batter into tube pan. Sprinkle with part of nut mixture.
Pour in remaining batter, then rest of nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dough for noodles or ravioli
directions: In a bowl, make a well in flour.
Add salt. Add eggs and water.
Mix until dough is well mixed.
Use flour to "clean" hands of all dough.
Place dough on lightly floured board. Knead until smooth.
Let stand 30 minutes to 1 hour before using to make ravioli or noodles.

title: bulgarian famous easy-bake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Beat the eggs and sugar at high speed for 5 minutes.
Add the flour and the vanilla and the grated lemon or orange skin.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into a buttered and floured pan or into small muffin pans.
Bake for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chocolate caramels
directions: Mix sugar, butter and syrup.
Boil until crack stage when dropped in water, then add chocolate, then nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cut the potatoes, cooked and peeled, in 1/2-inch pieces. Layer in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole with the brown sugar, salt and butter. Bake, uncovered, at 375° about 30 minutes or until glazed. Add a few marshmallows the last 5 minutes and brown slightly.

title: broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour into baking dish.
Crumble several Ritz crackers and cover top of broccoli mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Chop pepper and tomatoes; add salt and let stand until liquid comes to top.
Drain off.
Add water to cover and cook until it changes color.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, flour and sugar together.
Add this to pepper and tomatoes; cook and stir until thick enough to spread.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Make filling:
In medium bowl, combine first 8 ingredients, turn into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Make batter:
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Mix with wooden spoon until smooth.
Drop in 9 portions over filling, spacing evenly.
Batter will spread during baking.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until peaches are tender.
Serve with cream.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs, bananas, nuts and dry ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: spiced cranberry-orange mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce, cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Refrigerate until thickened, about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in diced orange.
Spoon into 5-cup mold.
Refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold. Makes 10 servings.

title: brunch quiche muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Use a cookie cutter or drinking glass to cut circular shapes. Line bottom and halfway up the side of muffin pan with pie dough. Sprinkle with onion and garlic powder, salt and pepper. Bake crust for 10 minutes. Combine in bowl the Egg Beaters, spinach, sun-dried tomatoes, chopped mushrooms and red pepper flakes. Fill muffins with egg mixture. Bake 29 minutes. Remove from oven. Add Swiss to top of each muffin and bake 10 more minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix thoroughly pumpkin, salt and spices.
Add milk to well beaten eggs.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Add sugar and bake in unbaked pie shell at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mizpah moravian chicken pie
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Skin and debone.
In pie crusts, put 3 cups of chicken and enough broth (about 3/4 cup).
Over the top of the chicken and broth, add several small pats of butter. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add tops and seal.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: spaghetti with meat and tomato sauce
directions: In a large saucepan heat the olive oil for 1 minute over moderate heat.
Add onion, carrot, celery and garlic.
Cook, stirring frequently until onion is soft for approximately 5 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon (set aside 1 tablespoon of salmon juice).
Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Mix egg and salmon together.
Add bell pepper and onions (salt is optional).
Add flour.
Mix together baking powder and salmon juice.
Add to ingredients and form into patties.
Place into hot grease.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pickles
directions: Mix and let come to a hard boil, then cut cucumbers and place in the jars with the salt, then pour the vinegar over cucumbers. Seal and put in a pot of hot water and let simmer over low heat for about 1 minute.

title: aried green plantains(dominican republic style)
directions: Peel plantains and cut in round pieces, 1-inch long.
Place oil in skillet and heat until very warm.
Place plantains round in oil. When oil is boiling, reduce heat and cook for a few minutes, until plantains are well cooked and begin to change from yellow to golden.
Remove plantains from oil.
With the bottom of a glass, smash each piece of plantain into cookie shape.
Turn heat to high and place plantains in oil.
Let them brown until golden.
Strain and place on paper towel.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Brown onion, celery and sausage.
Prepare stuffing mix per instructions on package.
Mix together.
Add applesauce.
Place in baking or serving dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, uncovered, until browned.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, syrup, nuts, salt, vanilla and chipped up butter or margarine.
Put into unbaked pie shell and bake about 50 minutes in oven at 325°.

title: garlic chip cookies
directions: Drop garlic cloves into boiling water for about 5 minutes until tender.
Peel and chop garlic and soak in maple syrup for 20 minutes.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Fold apples into mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon, sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt katie's chocolate cake
directions: Cream the sugar, lard, cocoa and eggs together, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Put batter into greased and floured pans and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray or grease Bundt pan.
Combine sugars and cinnamon in large bowl or large plastic bag.
Cut biscuits into quarters and toss with sugar mixture until well coated.
Line Bundt pan with biscuits, adding nuts as you fill the pan.
Mix remaining sugar mixture with butter.
Pour over biscuits.
Cook 30 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes and invert onto platter or rack to serve.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Grease 9 X 13 pan, make meatballs.
Mix 1 can Golden mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover with tinfoil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes and uncovered for 20 minutes.

title: lorraine's angel food torte
directions: Mix
Jell-O,
sugar and hot water.
When it is cool and it congeals, beat until stiff.
Fold in whipped cream or Dream Whip. Add
fruit and cake, broken up in small pieces.
Put in spring-form pan and chill several hours.

title: pineapple salad(excellent with ham)
directions: Drain pineapple juice into saucepan.
Add sugar and flour. Mix well.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cube cheese and mix with pineapple chunks.
Pour sauce over cheese and pineapple.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: stove top cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a saucepan.
Cook until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat and cook 1 minute. Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oats.
Stir well and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together and set aside.
In a saucepan, combine butter, shortening, cocoa powder and water.
Bring to a full boil.
Remove from the heat and mix in buttermilk, soda, vanilla and eggs.
Add all of this to the sugar and flour mix. Pour into well oiled and floured pan.
Bake at 400° until done (toothpick comes out clean).

title: french dressing
directions: Blend in mixer or blender.
Makes 1 quart.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Place beans in crock-pot or slow cooker.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until beans are tender, for several hours.
Serve over cooked rice.
This is very good served with blue tortilla chips.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: This can be made with other nuts.

title: bible cake
directions: Blend together butter, sugar, spices and salt.
Beat egg yolks and add.
Sift in baking powder and flour.
Add water and honey. Chop with chopper the fruit and nuts.
Flour them well.
Beat ingredients together thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: orange-kissed beets
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, cook and stir orange juice, brown sugar, margarine, cornstarch, ginger, salt and pepper until thick.
Add beets and raisins.
Heat thoroughly.
Garnish with orange peel.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Soften cheese and add other ingredients.
Low-fat!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp and crab dip
directions: Melt cheese and butter on low heat. Mix everything together until hot, then put in a dish and cover. Put in refrigerator.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a 3-quart baking dish, combine soup, milk and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until mixture is bubbly.
Meanwhile, cut each biscuit into quarters. Remove dish from oven; stir.
Arrange biscuit pieces over hot chicken mixture.
Bake 15 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Makes 5 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Mix dry ingredients, then mix with buttermilk.
Add yeast and knead lightly.
Place in refrigerator until needed.
Roll out and cut the amount needed.
Place on a pan 1 hour to let rise before putting into oven.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: catalina chicken breast
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Take from bone.
Have dough ready to roll real thin.
Put them in chicken mixture and cook until done.

title: chunky cream cheese french toast
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cube bread and cream cheese. Place both in greased pan. In a blender or with beaters, mix eggs, milk, syrup and butter. Pour over cubed bread and cream cheese. Cover with Saran Wrap overnight or for several hours. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 40 minutes or until golden brown and puffy. Serve with hot maple syrup. Serves approximately 6 to 8 people.

title: cherry delicious
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread cherry pie filling in a shallow, buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread dry cake mix evenly over cherries and top with almonds.
Pour butter evenly over the top and bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together in a large bowl the sugar and flour.
Mix in saucepan the oleo, shortening, cocoa and water and bring to a rapid boil.
Pour over dry ingredients. Stir well. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in a 16 x 11-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese-n-spinach casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Combine cheeses, spinach and eggs. Combine cooked noodles with spaghetti sauce and place half of the noodles on bottom of 3-quart casserole dish.
Top noodles with mixture; top with remaining noodles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: make and freeze meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix with hands until well combined. Form into about 60 (1-inch) meatballs.
Arrange in a single layer in a 12 x 8-inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper.

title: mud hens
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Spread thin in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put nuts on top of dough.
Beat the two egg whites until stiff; add 1 cup brown sugar.
Spread on top of nuts.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: uncooked fondant
directions: Mix margarine, corn syrup, salt and sugar well.
Divide. Knead in flavorings and appropriate colorings.
Shape into small balls; flatten.
Garnish with pecans, cherry halves, walnuts, etc.

title: red-stewed beef(also good for venison)
directions: Cook in crock-pot on low for 10 hours or in oven at 325° for 4 hours.
Serve with sauce.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt. In another bowl, beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla. Add flour mixture to egg mixture. Mix well. Fold in apples and pecans. Bake at 350° in a 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes or longer. Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: thelma's fruit punch
directions: Mix well and serve over ice.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Layer fruit in buttered baking dish with apple rings on top. Boil juice, sugar, margarine and cornstarch until thickens.
Cool and pour over fruit.
Bake 30 minutes at 250° until bubbly.

title: shrimp and broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small flowerets.
Cut green onions into small pieces.
Mix mayonnaise, Zesty Italian dressing and onion in bowl.
In larger bowl, combine broccoli, shrimp and dressing and mix well.
Ready to serve, but best if chilled for about 1 to 3 hours.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: In a large skillet cook beef, onion and pepper until vegies are tender.
Drain the grease.
Add soups, water and garlic. Blend with cheese and cooked spaghetti.
Top with additional cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole(georgia style)
directions: Mix the above and bake in oven at 375° for 40 minutes.
I suggest you divide the mixture in half and freeze for a later date.
Freezes well.

title: best lemon pie
directions: Mix together well.
Pour into graham cracker ready-crust. Makes 2 pies.
Very good!

title: cole slaw or potato salad(to keep on hand)
directions: Combine the ingredients in order until well blended.
If too thick, add more canned milk, vinegar and sugar to taste.
Pour over cabbage, potatoes or macaroni.
If there is any leftover, it can be stored in the refrigerator for a long time.
This is good to keep on hand all summer.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Cover bottom of an 11 x 17-inch pan with roll dough, patting and stretching to fit (sealing perforations). Brush lightly with melted margarine and dash of garlic salt. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until brown. Cool.

title: quick potatoes au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a casserole dish. Layer potatoes with onion in dish.
Melt butter in microwave in a microwave-safe bowl.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir; add milk. Heat in microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Return to microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir again.
Pour over potatoes. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour (or until potatoes are tender). Top with grated cheese.

title: pop's vinasnitzel(venison)
directions: For each egg, add 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and a dash of soy sauce.
Mix gently.
Cut meat into 2-inch squares, beat thin, dredge in egg mixture and roll in cracker meal.
Fry over medium heat.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend 1 cup flour, oleo and 1/2 cup sugar and press into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: ham rolls
directions: Slice the rolls into two sections and cover the bottom section with slices of American cheese and ham.
Put the top section back on top.
Stir the first 5 ingredients and dribble over the 2 pans of rolls.
May be made the night before and refrigerated.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cover meat with flour, salt and pepper.
Fry in small amount of oil until 1/2 cooked.
In pan, cover with onions.
Blend rest of ingredients; pour over meat and onions.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: banana split cake-dessert
directions: Mix together and press in pan.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Slice apples and soak in unsweetened pineapple juice to prevent them from turning brown. Arrange on platter when ready to serve.

title: mini blintzes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream egg yolks, 1/4 cup of the sugar and cream cheese.
Cut crusts from bread.
Roll each slice thin with rolling pin.
Spread with cream mixture.
Roll and dip with melted butter and then in cinnamon and sugar mix.
Cut pieces in half and freeze.
Bake until brown, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: czechoslovakian cabbage and beef soup
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat.
In soup pot add all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Stir frequently.
Add less water for a thicker soup; add other favorite spices, if desired.
Freezes well.

title: mom's famous macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in deep frying pan over medium heat.
Stir in flour until completely mixed.
Slowly add milk while stirring, until a white sauce develops.
Add pepper and keep stirring until thick.
Reduce heat to low.
Slowly add sharp Cheddar and Swiss slices, stirring until cheese mixes with sauce.
Bring 2 quarts water to a rolling boil.
Add macaroni, stirring occasionally until tender.
Drain noodles and return to pot.
Add cheese mixture and stir thoroughly.
Pour macaroni and cheese into large 9 1/2 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover macaroni and cheese with a thin layer of Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: japanese fried rice
directions: Cook the rice following the instructions on the package. This should take about 20 minutes. Pour the rice into a large bowl to let it cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Remove chicken from the bone and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix margarine, flour and buttermilk or sweet milk.
Bring soup and broth to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over chicken. Pour flour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown, then at 450° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 8.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in heavy saucepan.
Gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 2 minutes.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks, until yolks are hot.
Stir yolks into hot mixture.
Boil 2 minutes more. Add butter and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature, covered with waxed paper pressed right onto custard.
Remove paper.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue, sealing to edges of shell.
Brown in preheated oven.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Bake a whole oven full of potatoes (Idahos are best).
Cool to room temperature and freeze on cookie sheets.
When frozen solid, pack in large plastic bag.

title: cucumber sticks
directions: Pare cucumbers; cut into sticks lengthwise.
Dry slices with paper towels.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dip in crumbs, then in beaten egg, then in crumbs again.
Fry in oil until golden brown.

title: brownie mix
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder, sugar and cocoa; stir well. Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Place in an airtight container.
Store in a cool, dry place or in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
Yields 16 cups.

title: caramel popcorn brittle
directions: In a large Dutch oven, combine sugar and water.
Cook over medium-low heat, without stirring, for 10 minutes or until sugar dissolves.
Cover, increase heat to medium and cook 1 minute. Cook, uncovered and without stirring, 12 minutes longer or until amber.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Add popped corn, marshmallows and peanuts.
Working rapidly, stir well and spread into a 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan, coated with nonstick spray. Let cool.
Break into pieces.
Store in an airtight container. Yields 1 3/4 pounds.

title: marilyn's easy eggplant
directions: Peel and dice onion, garlic and eggplant.
Saut onion and garlic in olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat until opaque.
Add eggplant evenly over onion.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add portobello evenly; cover and reduce heat.
Cook stirring occasionally until vegetables are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add pesto sauce and serve.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.

title: old fashion tea cakes like mama made
directions: Sift flour into a large bowl.
Make a hole in the middle.
Put all ingredients in the hole in flour and add 1/3 cup buttermilk. Mix enough flour to make a stiff dough as you combine all ingredients with your hands.
Roll the dough on a board and cut with a large cookie cutter.
Bake on cookie sheet at 425°.
Bake until done but not too hard.
Never roll dough too thin because no one likes tea cakes that resemble cookies.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Fry chicken; add cream of mushroom soup and simmer until chicken is tender.

title: duncan hines apple pie
directions: Roll half of pastry to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface; fit into a 9-inch pie plate.
Set aside.

title: butterhorns
directions: Put yeast and sugar in the half cup warm water; let stand about 10 minutes or until all is melted.
Scald cup of milk and pour over shortening.
Add salt.
Beat eggs slightly.
When milk and shortening are cool, add yeast mixture, eggs and flour; beat slightly.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Turn out on mixing board.
Divide in four parts.
Roll out each piece thin like pie crust.
Spread with melted butter.
Cut in 8 wedges like you'd cut a pie.
Roll up beginning at outside of wedge.
Roll toward center.
Lay on baking sheet.
Brush with butter.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 or 20 minutes.
Makes 32 butterhorns.

title: butternut chews
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with butter flavor Crisco.
Beat eggs until light and foamy in large bowl. Beat in sugar, vanilla and Crisco until creamy.
Combine flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix at low speed until blended.
Stir in nuts at low speed (mixture will be stiff).

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Slice apples into bottom crust.
Cook apple juice, cornstarch and cinnamon until thickened.
Pour over apples.
Add top crust and sprinkle with additional cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach tortilla roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Spread on a tortilla. Roll up and wrap.
Continue until all filling is used.
Freeze. Cut frozen rolls into slices and allow to thaw slightly before serving.
May be stored frozen for three months.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Chop in blender for 2 or 3 seconds all ingredients except spices.
Tie spices up in cheesecloth and put into pot of mixture. Cook slowly until thickness desired.
Put into canning jars, seal and water bath, boiling for 10 minutes.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into muffin tins lined with cupcake papers. Freeze until firm. Store in plastic bags in freezer. MAKES 1 1/2 DOZEN CUPS.

title: potato soup
directions: In a 4-quart pot, mix margarine and flour over low heat; slowly add chicken broth, stirring until smooth.
Stir in milk. Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer for a couple of hours on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
10 servings.
